author: Yiming Ou
title: Cool looking wireless earbuds
content: These things does not really look like the Apple Airpods, but still looks pretty cool. Way better looking than a lot of wireless earbuds around. The sound quality is pretty good. Would not fall off your ears. I run with them and they stay in my ears perfectly. The battery life is long and charges fast.

author: J. Branche
title: Quality bluetooth earbuds
content:
Great Bluetooth earbud alternative to Airpods.  The sound is great, battery seems to last at least 1 1/2 hours but I have never run them out of battery yet.  They fit my ear good and the volume is great, even enough to hear over jet engine noise on flight.  Seems to be a good quality pair of earbuds and charging case.  I've purchased 2 pairs of the Competitors earbuds/NOT this brand and on one the charging port broke the other one earbud had half battery life and kept disconnecting.

Very happy I took a chance and bought these earbuds and enjoying using them all the time.

author: Amazon Customer
title: Does NOT work with IPHONE 11...yet
content:
These earbuds arrived quickly and were just as promised. They connected easily to multiple phones in my household and sounded good. However, they did NOT work with the iPhone 11s, which is what the teen that wanted them had.
  I posted this question on Amazon, since apparently the only mention of the issue is found in microscopic print under one picture in the description (I had to screenshot and enlarge it to see this). To my surprise, within a few days, the seller responded directly with an explanation, so bonus points for the seller. When they are updated to work with the newest iPhone, I may buy again. For now, I've returned them (which was also super easy @ Kohl's).

author: Makaio
title: Working great
content: These are great. Stay in my ears and connect effortlessly. Seems like a legit alternative to apples pricey product. They do seem to phase out a little here but not in a big way.

author: vinod singh
title: Headphones with incredible sound and advanced features.
content: I received this product today and the moment I opened the box, it took me few seconds to pair them to my phone. The sound quality was on par with expensive headphones out there in market. The built in push buttons is nice for one touch pairing and the low latency connection was very helpful in minimizing the audio lag while watching videos. Easily at 65% volume I have got 4 hours and 10 min and battery life is very good as promised. Definitely recommending to anyone out in market looking for a good quality and durable true wireless headphones for an affordable price.

author: Carlos Daniel González Alvarado
title: These earphones perform great from time to time.
content:
These earphones perform great from time to time.

Sometimes, the audio cuts constantly,  or stays in only one of the earphones.
It's pretty disappointing because these are not cheap. From time to time they work fantastically without any cuts or one-sided hearing. But the issues seem to be unfixable.

author: Nate
title: Great sound quality!
content: W O W.  Have never heard such good quality out of 40 dollar headphones!  These are almost as good as my Grados!  Purchased these for work, was a little hesitant due to the fact that my ears are smaller than normal and I’m frequently getting up and down.  While they are a little larger than the average headphone they fit just fine.  Cannot recommend them enough!

author: Michael Onwuegbuzie
title: Surprisingly sounds good
content: Pairing with my phone was easy, the sound quality was amazingly great, was skeptical before the purchase, but was surprised at how good they sounded. The case came in already charged but I still went ahead and charged it until the lights went off. Overall am happy with this earbuds, I will keep my fingers crossed and see how well they perform over time.

author: Edward V
title: Quality comparable to AirPods - Good set of earbuds for a good price
content:
I’ve been using these for a couple hours now, and my initial impressions of these wireless earbuds are of pleasant surprise and content. I wasn’t expecting an AirPod experience with these, but that’s what I got. And I mean that as a compliment: I LOVE my AirPods and I wouldn’t replace them for anything in the world. But, it is nice to have a spare set of wireless earbuds to keep in your day bag or gym bag, and I can definitely say these earbuds can fill that role.

Sound quality is actually pretty good compared with the AirPods, but there is a slight difference(more on this further down) like there isn’t as much bass compared to the AirPods; This could be either a positive or negative depending on who you’re asking. But, for the most part, if you were to blind-test me just in music quality alone, I wouldn’t be able to tell the difference unless I was really paying attention.

Next thing I want to talk about is how these fit in my ears. They are noticeable larger and fit more snugly in my ear compared to the slimmer AirPods. And this is probably why I wasn’t get as much of a bass response compared to the AirPods because these earbuds seemed to not make as good a seal as the AirPods did for my ears. But that of course just comes down to my personal ear shape; Any earbud that doesn’t have adjustable  silicon tips is always something you gotta “buy it to try it” sort of deal. But on that note, if you feel that the AirPods were a bit on the small side for your ears, then these earbuds might be able to fit you better.

Button ergonomics and UX are good. The buttons are tactile and have a satisfying click to them. Single click to pause/play, long click on the left earbud to backtrack, long click on the right earbud to skip forward. It’s very intuitive and drama-free.

Pictures are attached comparing the AirPods(left) and these earbuds(right). You can really see the size differences. From a normal viewing distance, it would be really easy to ‘fool’ anyone into thinking you’re wearing actual AirPods.

If there is anything more to note through more long term usage, I’ll update my review here.

author: Dan Kim
title: Good quality wireless headset
content:
It’s really difficult to not compare this with AirPods. As a stand-alone unit these headsets are decent.  The sound quality is surprisingly very good.  Much better than my TWSi500 AirPod clones.  The connectivity and range is also great.  Battery life also seems good.

My biggest qualms is that it falls short on everything else compared to AirPods.

-no wireless charging case
-more round-about way if syncing then connecting
-no battery life indicator

Also an inconvenience that it uses Micro USB instead of lightning or usb C.

If you’re simply looking for something that works this is great solution.  If you’re like me and trying to go from AirPods to this it’s tough.

author: Dan Paul
title: Terrible fit.
content: Terrible.  Won't stay in my ears. Also cause pain after awhile if constant pushing them back into place.  Ridiculous.

author: Valerie
title: really good!
content:
I just got these and tried them and honestly loooove them.
They fit nicely in my ear, they are not like those in-ear earbuds that I find really uncomfortable (but that for some reason seem to be the only type around unless you want to buy apple), and they are priced decently, and far from the expensive Ipods. The sound seems good, the little case is very cute and easy to carry around, and it is very useful that it automatically recharges the earphones. I only miss a volume control on the earphones and will see how long the battery last!

author: Kishore Sherigar
title: Awesome Earbuds..!!!
content: I was very impressed with this product. I bought similar apple earbuds look alike in the past and they were very disappointing. They were either too big or don’t pair correctly or they break fast. This pair on the other hand was exceptional. The quality of sound is Stereo 5.0 superior quality. Making phone calls quality is great. They fit perfectly. The charging case and battery life are awesome.The earbuds tell you when the connect or loose the connection! The sound quality is very, very good. The ear buds seem to last quite awhile on a charge. I have yet to run them down in a single session. The volume is loud enough to hear while cycling on my indoor trainer which is very much appreciated! I had to wear ear muffs over my old ones to be able to hear audio while riding. No way to adjust volume from the buds, but I can deal with that. I like that they can be used individually. I forgot the left one was the Master and turned the right one off. The left one continued to operate. That is actually pretty cool. I was even able to turn the right one back on. Upon receiving, I noticed just how nicely packed they were and how cute the little charging case is, which is small and can fit in my pocket without looking bulky. They're easy to set up after reading the user manual, which I recommend, so I could figure out how to change songs, pause, or go back to a previous song. I haven't received any calls while using these, so I can't say how well the Bluetooth works for that, but I have high expectations. The sound quality is amazing and blocks out outside noises, which is great but also dangerous if you're outside and can't hear cars coming by, so definitely make sure you're paying attention to your surroundings. Overall, I'm really impressed with these earbuds and highly recommend these if you're looking for cheaper headphones without paying Apple's prices!!More importantly, it’s the looks. It’s simple and neat, unlike other true wireless products with complicated designs on the box and the earbud. This pair of earbud is suitable for any circumstance. Plus on the charger of the earbud which is the case shows the battery status of the earbuds. I compared with many other sellers, they actually don’t have this feature on their products. The connection for these earbuds is surprisingly simple. They connect automatically when I pool them out once the first-time connection is done. Overall I highly recommend these earbuds. It’s really a good deal!!!

author: Bryleigh Clark
title: Surprisingly good decent headphones
content: This is my 1st and hopefully only wireless earbuds. I like the option of being able to share my earbud if need be and not have to stand while the other person is listening. They were easy to charge and the charge was quick. Syncing them to my devices was also easy. The sound quality is great. Music is clear and the vear is nice. Using them for calls was great as well. I could hear clearly and I can adjust the volume easily. Other callers made mention that there was no distortion or issues hearing me as I moved around. So I like these earbuds.

author: oherc
title: Very nice, have to hide these from my wife
content: I like these more than my Samsung buds. They stay in my ear when I'm working and sweaty. They are much louder too so I guess you don't need noise canceling technology! They hold a charge long I haven't had to charge them during day but if you open cover and put them in they glow orange to let you know they are charging. Also you can use either one or both! Very nice. I'm surprised and happy

author: Ramya
title: Great quality earbuds
content:
My previous set of bluetooth headphones had lost their ability to hold a charge, so I looked at buying new ones. I was only looking for something which would have decent sound quality and reasonable isolation, and something which would have better battery life. These were on sale, so I decided to give them a try.
Not only do these fit incredibly comfortably, but the sound quality is very good. There's a tiny amount of background hiss (as is typical for actively powered headphones) but it's low enough that it doesn't interfere with my enjoyment of the music, and it does serve a purpose in letting me know they're turned on.
The little charging/carrying case is nicely designed. It has enough battery to charge the earbuds 4 times, and it also itself can be charged wirelessly or via USB. All in all these are great little earbuds and are well worth the money.

author: Speaker40
title: Almost as good a iPods, great for the price
content: I had the real ones and had them stolen, so I thought I would try these because they are So much more affordable.These hold a good charge and I like the magnetic contacts that hold the earbuds in place while they are charging. Once I have paired it to my iPhone, I just take them out of the case and they power on and pair automatically. When done, I just pop them back in the case and they automatically turn off and begin charging wherever you are. It’s so easy, hard to be more convenient than that. The fit and sound are good. Very clear. Bass is lacking,but that is also the same with other ear buds I have used in the past. Hoping these last longer than my ipods did.

author: Cindy Tran
title: Affordable earbuds
content: This earbud is almost a replica of Apple AirPods but at a more affordable price. I love the look of this earbuds. I can wear these at home to watch movies easily. The only downside of this earbud is it’s not as comfortable when you wear it for a few hours. It is also a little big for my ear as well. Overall, I really love this version of the earbud.

author: Bassman999
title: Convenient, great sound, long lasting battery.
content:
These are really nice earbuds.
No problem staying in during my morning walk/runs.
I can still hear traffic and an aware of my surroundings, but the music is still clear and loud.
There case is like a smooth sided dental floss package.
Easily fits in my pocket and won't scratch my phone screen.
When I'm done I just drop them in the case and they recharge automatically from there lithium battery in the storage case.
It's been about a week and i haven't had to recharge them yet because the storage case battery still has plenty of life left.
If you have any issue with these stand in your ear make sure that your ears aren't oily inside because these are smooth.
This means there are no rubber pads to fall off but you do need to make sure to keep them from being oily so they stay in.
These look similar to AirPods but cost about 1/3 the price. They sound just as good to me.

author: Leslie T.
title: Great quality ear buds
content:
I really like these.  I can make hands free calls easily.  I can listen to Music while I work.  The sound is very clear.  They paired easily with iPhone and Android.

The battery charger lasted me all day.

author: Jean
title: Mixed feelings but awesome sound quality!
content:
Overall, the product itself was pretty high quality. I had also bought another brand and I can see how these are way better. The case is just like Apple's, a little bigger, pretty durable. The earbuds themselves are comparable to Apple's as well. I was surprised at how good the sound the was and the instant connection to my phone was awesome. As soon as I take them out, they were connected to my phone. Functions were easy to forward/skip or stop.

The only problem for me was when I used them to talk on the phone, the person on the other end could not hear me unless I had the earbuds right in front of my mouth. I did a test call myself and found that unless it was in front of my mouth, you couldn't hear anything on the other end. I was very disappointed because other than that, the earbuds were awesome and for the price. I ended up giving them to my husband cause he said he was happy using them just for music. However, when he uses them, I can hear him just fine...So I don't know why it didn't work so well for me. So for him, he's very pleased with them.

author: Todd Thomas
title: Great battery life.
content: I like that they stay in my ears. These style don’t usually do that for me. Battery lasts a long time. The sound is great, but I can’t go running in these, they’ll fall out (probably because of my small ears). So I like them for around the house and in coffee shops. Also like the case, really small.

author: Joe R
title: Product battery life is misrepresented on Amazon
content: Product battery life is misrepresented on Amazon. Product manual says 3 hours (see image). On Amazon it’s advertised as 4-5 hour battery life. Returned Product.

author: Steve Songster
title: Excellent Purchase
content: I purchased these Bluetooth earbuds in my quest to find the best earbuds at a reasonable price.  I get up very early in the morning and listen to music, watch TV and movies on my PC and use the earbuds so the sound does not wake my wife.  I am especially pleased with the sound.  The ear piece fits remarkably tight for a solid one-piece design.  The earbud charge lasts long enough to watch a 2 hour movie and still not need charging.  The very convenient small charging case will fit nicely in your pocket.  Very fast recharge.  Very easy to setup and use.

author: Raptor
title: good for the size
content:
over the years I've tested quite a few headphones, these fit a specific need, they are small and discreet, have decent sound, and work ok in higher noise environments while still allowing some outside noise. i tested them while driving with the roof off and windows down and i could still enjoy the new tool album in the earbuds.

are they going to be as good as studio grade headphones. no, will they be perfect to stick in a pocket and use on a commute. absolutely. these are going to be my go to travel earphones.

they stayed in just fine, and sound decent. listened for about an hour and they still had quite a bit of battery left.

author: Ashley
title: Great alternative to airpods
content: These are very sleek and perfect for the alternative to expensive air pods I was looking for. They stay in my ears well. The sound is pretty good but not exceptional (which I wouldn’t expect from $30 earbuds lol). Overall I’m happy with them!

author: Siyi
title: Good sound, quick connection, small case, good sound
content: These earbuds stay well in my ear, though there are not size choices, so it may not work for everyone. I have tried others that kept falling out of the ear. The case is small so easy to keep on hand to recharge. The sound is good, though I have only used so far for podcasts and audio book. The connection is made immediately upon taking them out of the case. So far I like these very much.

author: BSJ
title: Bargain Buy!
content: Great product for the price! Did not want to shell out the $$$ for AirPods but these work super well and are a guilt-free purchase. Incredibly easy to pair and to use. Charging case is beautiful. Earbuds slightly bulkier than the AirPods but are comfortable. Charger compatible with any standard USB or wall plug. Would buy again!

author: ~*~JillyB~*~
title: Just what I was looking for
content: These Bluetooth EarPods are great. They hold a charge very well and connect immediately upon taking them out of their case. Finally found a decent alternative to pricey Apple’s EarPods.

author: YKY BUY
title: Decent budget true wireless earbuds
content: I tried this product for a couple days. It's a very decent product at this price range. The bluetooth is easy to connect and sound quality is good enough for your daily use and workout. The battery is long enough within my expectation. I plan to use it for my daily call on the go!

author: BaileyHkin
title: Very Nice airpods alternative.
content: The reason I like the airpods type that don't go in your ears is because I can still hear what is going on around me. These work seamlessly both in mono and stereo mode. Have worked great at work. I can still hear out of the ear I have it in.  My only complaint is that it used micro USB and not usb C but that is not a big deal. I had one in for a few hours with no battery issues so battery life is a 10/10 from me.

author: Faith
title: Great quality headphones
content: These are really great bluetooth headphones, they fit my ears perfectly (my smaller friend did say they were a little big for her though) the sound quality is great, better then I expected for the price. They are very comfortable which is super important to me as I have been having problems with the fully in the ear bluetooth headphones and these fixed that for me! They look very similar to the apple ones but are obviously way cheaper. The charging case came fully charged and I have yet to have to charge it after a full week of use. I have not yet had the headphones die on me while using them either so I can say the battery life is really good. Great headphones at a nicely affordable price!

author: AJ
title: Too Good for the Price
content:
I am trying some Wireless earbuds as have a big family.. have used several of them available and was little skeptical about this one.. however, they are good and stand out.

Would buy another as it is a good gift option too.

Have been using for 2 days and so far all good.

author: Marchsnow
title: Good quality earbuds in affordable price
content:
Look-wise:
The earbuds looks very similar to Apple AirPods.  Compare to AirPods, This charging case is slightly larger in all dimensions but rounder and puffier.  Its ear pods are also overall slightly larger, and the shape somewhat similar to AirPods but not identical.  It looks and feels good, and the mechanism is great, too.

Sound Qualified wise:
This earbud is easy to operate like most other wireless earphones, but it produces better stereo and microphone results than many others.

When compare to regular Apple EarPods, Thr earbuds sounds just as good.  However, its microphone transmitting quality and clarity are a little beneath regular EarPods’.  Which is understandable, due to the microphone location is much higher up then EarPods’.

Use time:
These rwrbuds performed a solid 4 hours of play time before they signaled a battery charging reminder through voice notification.

On the other hand, The charing case charges quickly.  It takes no mare then 2 hours to fully juice up.

Downside:
There is one tiny downside for these earbuds — When more then one device has been connected to it and both are in range, user needs to first disconnect from the previous device in order to connect to the next one.

author: MO
title: Better than you would ever expect!
content: A great feature of this product has is how it automatically connects to the device that was last used as soon as the case is open. The latch of the case is held by magnets and these have a very comfortable fit. The sound quality is awesome! The buttons on the earbuds for additional functions help. So far, these earbuds are haven’t let me down. These have a very good look to them. The battery life in a row is such a long time. I once used them for a straight 45 minutes and these didn’t even die out once! I am very satisfied with my purchase.

author: Rhiannon
title: My top 3 bluetooth
content: I've purchased a lot of different kinds of Bluetooth to find the right one and these are my top 3. They stay in your ear and does not fall out like most do. The sound is clear and the bass is deep.

author: Mayur Pise
title: AirPods for Pixel XL 🙂
content: We have 2 Pixel XL devices, my wife wanted AirPods but with price tag and compatibility with Android we not able to buy those. So wanted to similar looks Bluetooth earpods and these are really live upto expectations. Light weight and sounds good. Recommend for Android users specially who can't use Apple AirPods.

author: JimE
title: Not Reliable!!!
content: They skip like an old record player. Just when you are exhausted and in the middle of a run or nice walk , they begin to go on and off (skipping). Be SURE and buy Amazon Insurance or a new pair of Apples.. Aggravating to say the least..

author: derek
title: Good sound quality!
content: Who would of thought that they are as good as Apple. Of course they aren’t apple, but when you have a 11 year old who wants a pair, these do the trick! They are in a charging case just and charge the same. The sound quality is great. Often she can’t hear me even yelling when she has them in her ears. I would recommend this product for anyone not wanting to pay the outrageous price of apple. Seller was helpful also. Kept in contact with my questions and concerns before I purchased. Also let me know that if I had any problems to let them know. Which made me feel confident about my purchase.

author: Ahmad Wahidy
title: Sound Quality
content: My nephew’s birthday is coming up and he has been bugging me for awhile to get him a pair of wireless earbuds. I bought this on a hunch it turned out to be a decent pair of headphones for the money you spend. Sound quality is great. But I am not satisfied with the size it’s a little big for ears and sometimes it falls off the ears. I am giving it five stars because the sound quality is great.

author: Vmuller2
title: Great sound quality
content: These earbuds fit perfectly in my ears without falling out while moving around. I love that I can both listen to music and take calls making them super convenient. The sound quality is super high quality and it has noise cancellation which is important. The microphone works really well and I’ve taken calls and the other person on the other line can hear me perfectly. I highly recommend them

author: Niqui Higbee
title: Pretty good buds!
content: I've been wanting to try wireless headphones for a while and these ones are pretty great the sound quality is really good and the distance you can walk away from your phone is pretty large before they disconnect or say out of range. It doesnt cancel out noise completely. The other thing is they won't fit well in someone who has super tiny ears but other than that they are good!

author: Karla Best
title: Just as good as "brands"
content: Work as advertised.. but they work well. The sound is good, they fit my ear well, and the battery actually lasts longer that 10 minutes, which is great. Good investment. You're not paying a crazy amount for a "name" and they are JUST as good!!

author: TechGuy
title: Stable connection, decent sound, decent battery life, okayish call quality
content: These are obviously Apple airpods lookalike but their size is a bit bigger (the earphone stem is thicker) compared to actual airpod. That being said, they are pretty light. They do have a cheap feeling but they sound just like most other bluetooth earbuds. I didn't run into battery depleting issues and their range is actually pretty good (probably because of Bluetooth 5.0). The case provides another 5-6 times charging so, it's definitely good for a week worth of workout sessions. For me personally, they don't stay in my ears if I move my head rapidly (just like Apple Airpods) but that may vary from person to person. Overall, it's a decent quality Airpod replacement for a pretty cheap price.

author: ibsharyn
title: Sadly disappointed
content:
I loved these ear buds and used them regularly for a few weeks.  After that time the right side only started making crackling sound that sounded like they were breaking.  I charged them overnight thinking maybe they were finally running out of battery.  The next day they lasted a few minutes, but the crackling sound started up again.  I tried to charge them again and give them a third try, but they still have the crackling sound only on the right side.  I contacted the seller to get a replacement and they said they were unable to but will issue a refund upon return.  I'm hoping they stand up to their end of the deal.
They were GREAT until they weren't. :(

author: Amazon Customer
title: Very well worth the money spent!
content: I ordered these earbuds last Friday and, they were not supposed to be here until Thursday. I received the earbuds one day early and, packaged very well. At my surprise I took the earbuds out of the case and they were 75% charged and, the case was 75% charged. As soon as I took the buds out of the case they turned on and, I went to the Bluetooth on my phone and, they paired and connected within 20 seconds. I'm also very impressed with the sound quality of these earbuds and would recommend the purchase to anyone that does not want to spend a fortune on wireless earbuds. Don't be fooled by the products that look like these and only cost twenty bucks. I ordered one of those and they don't work very well at all. The additional twenty bucks I spent for these is very well worth it. I have a friend who has an iPhone and he bought the airpods. I've listened to them and, these sound just as good. Get them and, enjoy!.

author: Veronica K. Martinez
title: Like air pods, but cheaper!
content: These are exactly what I was looking for. They look very similar to air pods, minus the huge price tag. I have an iPhone, and have no problem connecting them. I’ve had them for 2 weeks now with constant use, they still work perfectly. The noise cancellation can be good, I don’t listen to stuff super loud normally. Both the case as well as the earbuds feel high quality. I’m very happy with these, and so happy I saved myself a ton of money.

author: Emily C. Dailey
title: Nope.
content:
I bought these after my Airpods were stolen out of my car last week. I figured they'd do the trick for a few months until I could get new Airpods. As soon as I unboxed them, I could tell the quality was so bad compared to Apple. I can tell you now, the only similarities between the two products is the shape of the case and earbuds themselves. The charging case feels very lightweight and cheap. I read the manual, and throughout the booklet, it references the "master" earpod, which is defaulted to the left piece. So I spent 10 minutes trying to get them to turn on and pair only to realize that my master earpod is actually the right one. Maybe something is wrong, or they changed the product and didn't update the directions. Once I charged them and was able to get them to pair, the left earpod would not turn on. Even after resetting them and going through the pairing process again, the left one will not work.

The feature I loved about Apple Airpods is the tapping capabilities that you can customize to support whatever command you want for each earbud. For example, I can decide if I want the left to pause my song, change the song, activate Siri, etc. and the same goes for the right. I thought this one would have a similar set up. On this brand, both have buttons on the earpod, and the directions just list the capabilities, but doesn't provide any instructions or clarification on which feature applies to which earbud. Considering I cannot even get the left one to work, I don't know if I'll even be able to figure out which purpose it serves.

I realize this is a Chinese product and I'm sure the English version of the manual is a rough translation of the Chinese directions on the back. However, some of my directions don't even make sense. For example, one section tells me that when the headphones are fully charged, the orange light on the case will turn off. In the section below that, it states the light will remain lit when they're fully charged. Apple Airpods have an pop-up window that appears on your screen indicating the battery life of your case, along with each individual earbud. Now I am just taking a guess as to whether or not this version is fully charged.

Definitely will be returning and buying new Airpods on Black Friday. This may be a great product for someone who has never had Airpods before, but in my opinion, the two just do not compare.

author: cbryan7
title: Better than expected sound and just really convenient
content:
I’m digging these headphones. Obviously most people will be comparing these to AirPods and since those are so widely owned I included a couple of pictures comparing them visually (AirPods on the right, Rademax are on the left). I was pretty hesitant about getting this style headphone until my wife got some AirPods and I found out why everybody is raving about wireless headphones like this! They are so quick, easy to use, comfortable, and just so dang convenient. So if you are like me and didn’t understand all the hype around wireless earbud headphones I suggest you try some out for yourself.
Now some helpful notes about these in particular, they fit in the ear slightly larger than AirPods so you need to know that. It wasn’t a problem for me and actually it creates a pretty snug fit. I tried head banging with them to test how secure they are and they didn’t budge! However my wife has small ears and these would not stay in for her. So I do not recommend these for people with small ears.
The sound quality is exactly what I hoped for. I’d say a bit better than most stock headphones that come with a phone. I didn’t throw these in expecting Bose or Beats over the ear style sound, I bought these for the convenience and ease of use and as long as the sound is better than average I’m a very satisfied customer, which I’m happy to say is the case for these!

author: Linda Le
title: Excited about this purchase!  Wireless Bluetooth Headset!!
content: I've been looking forward to this product for some time now and it did not fail.  I haven't used it till it ran out of batteries but I'll have a chance in a few months when I go on an overseas trip with over 24 hour travel time and no charging opportunities. :D  What I'm excited most is that I'll be able to listen to music or watch videos without anyone noticing! LOL

author: Kristine Bullen
title: Too big for my small ears
content: They seemed to work great; however, they were quite large and wouldn't stay in my ears. My sons airpods are smaller and fit in my ears fine but these didn't. Probably perfect if you have large ears. Not perfect for me. :) Returned them.

author: Evan
title: High value earphones
content: You definitely get the bang for your buck with these earphones. My wife and I own three pairs of wireless earphones between us. This pair by far has the best sound quality. The battery life is the lowest of the three but the carrying case also serves as a charger for some extra juice in between charges. The shape of the earphones is very similar to the earphones that come with new iPhones. Those earphones don’t fit well for me but are perfect for the wife so it would be a good way to check if these will fit before you buy them. Recommended +++

author: Viz-Vin
title: in expensive alternate for AirPods
content: First I got it because it fits like Apple AirPods and it is lot within the budget. The style is similar to AirPod as you see it in picture attached. The size is slightly bigger and as dedicated buttons to receive and play next songs . The only drawback of the earphones is it doesn't get auto disconnected when I put it the charging case. However, it is still manageable for the deal price under $45

author: LaDon Solise
title: Perfect gift for Christmas
content: I bought these for my almost 11 year old son.  My daughter has the apple version so I had her try these out.  While the case is a little larger and the ear buds are a little thicker than hers, she liked the sound quality better.  I bought these for my son for Christmas but now I'm thinking I may order myself a pair as well =)

author: Cirien
title: Wireless earbuds in a compact case
content: These Bluetooth earbuds come with a small, white charging case. I was able to find them easily on bluetooth and pair them with my phone. The earbuds light up when placed inside the charging case, and the charging case comes with a micro USB cable that plugs into the bottom. Overall, these were easy to setup and use.

author: Bhumika palesha
title: Recommended !!
content: The sound quality is great. The connectivity is easy as well and works perfectly fine with any phone. It’s looks very similar to the apple airpods model however the difference is noticeable on a closer look. But overall love the aesthetics as well as the quality of this product

author: khristinmd
title: Good sound and very pocket handy
content: Definitely the sound is high in quality. Pairing was super easy and the color is white which looks so clean. It’s handy and can be put in the pocket to bring anywhere. This is good for gifting this holiday season.

author: Jennifer Watson
title: Comfort without the silicone
content: These headphones are real comfortable. I was a little nervous being that there are no extra silicone pieces to find the right fit- and I have smaller ears and so I have found a lot of earbuds uncomfortable in the past.  What I like is there is no silicone piece as those get lost in my house constantly. (I am not sure if it is the kids or they just fall off). It is nice to know I won’t have to worry about losing a piece to make it fit comfortably.  They come in a nice small charging case so you can charge them while you are on the go. The battery life lasts a long time. It was easy to set up and use. They have good sound coming from them. It’s a great set!

author: Nikki
title: Nice sound quality and long battery life.
content: The quality is pretty good and is comparable to the higher priced name brand earbuds. The earbud, when playing music, last anywhere from 3-4.5 hours before they need a charge. When you put them in your ear you can not feel that they are there. They are very comfortable and they stay put. My one issue is the left earbud would die 15min faster than the right earbud How I fix this problem is I press and hold the multifunctional key on both earbuds right before I charge them- you will hear them say "power off". I also make sure to plug the usb in the wall even though they can charge directly from the case. I charge then though the case with out USB if I am out. I also put the earbuds in the charging case together so they charge and drain at the same speed.  So far I really like them.

author: Paul
title: Credible MIC QUALITY!
content:
I was amazed at this earbud's performance, especially the microphone quality. I have used many earbuds before, galaxy earbuds, airpods, jabra elite. Among them the best sounding microphone was airpods, although I would not praise its audio quality. I was looking into some cheaper bluetooth earbuds and want to see if the high price of previous mentioned earbuds are necessary? So I came by this earbud and honestly I had my doubts even before I got to try them out. I thought, for such a price, how good can it be. However, the sound was amazing, I would not say that its on the bass side of the spectrum, but the mid and the highs are clear. I made many phone calls and out of 10 people 8 people said they can understand my words with no problem. The other two mentioned that they can understand me fine, but they sometimes had to use context clues to put them all together. I say that this earbud for its price is a great LIGHT earbud and a great choice for those wanting a quality sounding earbuds. The only problem that I had with this is that the connector is MICRO USB... I mean I can live with it but its just another wire to carry along with me. LETS GO USB C PLEASE!!

Overall I enjoy using these earbuds for its quality sound for music and me having confidence that people will understand fir sure during phone calls. Awesome earbuds.

author: Nathaniel
title: Quality wireless earbuds
content: These wireless earbuds are very nice. Very comfortable in the ear. Great sound quality, and the button controls are helpful too. The in-case charging is also really cool. Battery life is very long, probably about 3-6 hours in my experience. I do wish that the Bluetooth connectivity range would be a little farther - the sound started to get choppy when I got about 15-20 feet away.

author: Neha
title: Good for the budget
content: Buy these earphones!!! These EarPods has amazing sound quality and a wireless charging case, everything that you need in budget. I have never used AirPods but till I do these are best.

author: Alan
title: They have static and cut out.
content: I'm a 60 year old male. They fit great, They are hard for me to get out of the charging case.  Were easy to connect to my phone.  I purchased two pair for me and my wife. One I Phone One Android both lose connection in one ear piece  and cut in and out.  Back to hard wire.

author: matthew blackburn
title: Very light, great sound and a awesome price!
content: As far as earbuds go I can say these are the most comfortable I’ve ever worn. They are very lightweight compared to what I’m used to. So light that hey feel like they might fall out but I can shake my head and they stay put, almost like some kind of earbud magic keeps them in place. Sound seems very clear with no distortion that I can tell. Seems like a quality product as best I can tell.

author: The Patel
title: Perfect fit for ear, its win for me.
content:
This is perfect earbuds for who wants very good fit in their ear rather than ANC.
And because of this it becomes very convenient to use for longer time.
I have several point of view on which this product 's over all rating is phenomenal. My list starts as below.

1. Latest BT-5.0 tech : which enables it to pair/connect instantaneously with targeted device, It has superior connectivity range. I keep on switching this buds whenever needing between my mobile and laptop( both has BT5.0), it works seemlessly-awesome.
2. Battery : This product has best thing happen with BT headsets in last couple of years, even though it has smaller life cycle - the carrying case becomes its battery backup, I usually uses this product for 2-3 hrs at straight and once I am done, just have to put it in its box, boom- battery start recharging again.
3. Look & Feel : It is nice slick product design, and ear buds fits way better than i have expected.
4. Sound : I would say this has great sound with best stereo who wants to watch videos and listen music on the go, why working out etc.,
5. Built in Mic :  I wont recommend this for long call or join audio meeting cause some of my friend has ask me to change my headsets number of times during call because there is constant drop in sound/ constant disturbance , I think this is the only drawback of this product.
6. Price point : Good price point for this product, best fit to my need and my usage.

I think they have also included 18 M warranty, so if something happens down the line with product we should good to go.

author: Mel
title: Sound quality better than others
content: I find these earbuds to be more comfortable than other hard-style air buds I have tried. The sound quality is really good, for both music and voice call quality. One thing that stood out is that the microphone is high quality compared to others I have used. Callers could easily hear and understand me on calls, which makes it good for using while participating in conference calls.

author: NSWAFFAR
title: Cute bluetooth earbuds.
content: Cute bluetooth earbuds. Similar look to AirPods, just a tad bit bigger. It is easy to pair, very easy. The sound quality is pretty good for the price. As for the range, it doesn't go too far. Right when I step off the outside the house it cuts off. But as long as I'm in the house and the phone is in the house, it stays on. So it's pretty good. My stepdaughter who wants an AirPods will love this. It's a good start up for a kid who doesn't know how to take care of her stuff yet.

author: ssjiahuiss
title: perfect replacement for airpods
content: I lost my AirPods and couldn't afford to buy another one. Found this product and it is the perfect replacement for my AirPods without paying $160! The sound quality is just as good as airpods but slightly bigger, it fits my ears though and I am 5ft 8 male. This earbud doesnt come with wireless case charging but neither does my airpods. I saved over $100 and I am pleased.

author: Ariel
title: Budget Airpods
content:
I like to workout but i also don’t want to risk breaking my more expensive AirPods. I looked online for cheaper alternatives and ended up with this. I couldn’t be happier as the earbud shape are very similar. The pairing is also as intuitive as AirPods so I find myself switching between these and AirPods all the time

The biggest con to this is the mic since a lot of my phones calls are pretty unclear. L But honestly, if you’re using AirPods to begin with, the mic for that isn’t all that glamorous either

author: Von Marie
title: Surprisingly Amazing!!
content:
I got these thinking I would have a literal knock off version of Airpods but these things really hold their own. First thing I noticed was it is made of really high qualify plastic. It didn't feel "cheap" at all. Second, the earbuds paired immediately as I opened the case! No lag in Bluetooth connection whatsoever. The earbuds themselves are pretty substantial compared to Apple earbuds but they fit my ears snuggly. If you have smaller ears these might be kind of big. I personally find Airpods and Apple earbuds a little small for my ears. I like the sound quality a lot, I don't notice much of a difference between these and my regular Apple buds. I like using these especially for phone calls because it makes moving around the house and taking calls VERY easy, with both buds in or just one.

Overall, it's a great buy for its price! The battery so far has lasted me a week and counting. Definitely recommend if you're looking for a Bluetooth bud alternative!

author: Steve M.
title: Easy pairing
content: Only have them a couple of days now and noted the fit isn't great, fall out when bending over to do something, easy to find though. Also the left ones charge doesn't last as long as the right. Wouldn't recommend to younger active people trying to get the Apple ipod look.

author: Beata G Osinski
title: Airpods for not even half the price!!
content: I wanted wireless headphones but the price of airpods is so high! I decided to try these since they had a bunch of reviews. They came super fast and the quality is excellent. They connect with my computer and my iphone with no problems. Now my husband wants to get a pair too! The case is super similar to airpods and the sound quality is exactly the same to me. My daughter has airpods and even she likes these.

author: Nghiem
title: Great value!
content: I was hesitant of spending $200 on brand new Airpods 2, so I went with these wireless earbuds. I can say it does the job for me! I listen to my Spotify occasionally when I am at work and at home. The feel of the buds are fitted and comfortable in the ears. I also used these to listen to soft instrumental music to help me fall asleep! If you are looking for wireless earbuds but not wanting to spend hundreds on the Airpods, I would suggest getting these wireless earbuds!

author: Abe
title: Decently priced, well built BT 5.0 earbuds
content: Sound quality is really good for the price. I have a few of these and this one I got for my wife. She has an iphone and apparently it pairs really good with hers. I've checked the sound multiple times and its flawless. She has been happy using it at the gym too. Its relatively stable in ear. The way I tested it, noise canceling can be a bit better since it's not one of those earbuds that fits into your ear 100%, but it does have noise cancellation and it's not a $300 bose noise canceling headphone. It's well built and is a good replacement for apple earbuds. Recommend!

author: Camilo Rueda
title: Love the way it looks and how it fits on my ears.
content: Love the white look to it, from a distance you can’t really tell the difference between this and apple earbuds. But aside from the look is very comfortable on the ear & adjust perfectly. Some other earbuds fall to easily but not this one, this one I could be jogging at a good pace and it would still be in my ear. The sound is also high quality, I’m able to hear smoothly even if I turn the volume high.

author: Jordan
title: Decent audio, friendly design, horrible microphone
content: I wanted to believe the overwhelmingly positive reviews on this, but once again I am disappointed with a product that falls short of what the reviews suggest. Albeit these earbuds aren't the worst quality out there; they have halfway decent audio for listening to podcasts or music and might be fine if that's all you need. However, I need to be able to take phone calls on these. This is a major feature I'm looking for and honestly the quality of the microphones on these is so bad they should have just left them off. For testing I called a couple friends who said they could barely hear me and that only some of my words came through. I had my wife put them on and call me with them and I confirmed they don't pick up everything that's being said. I read the user manual that comes in the box hoping I could adjust their sensitivity perhaps, but the manual only offers a method to reset back to factory settings. I tried that but it made no difference. These are getting returned.

author: Vu
title: Should try it !
content: This earbuds at first glance looks like an Apple airpods, so I like that, because the price is much cheaper than airpods.  It has a nice design, warm sound.  but the weight is a bit light, so the quality doesn't look perfect.

author: Wojtek
title: Good sound quality but mediocre mic
content: I generally liked those very much but i got them primarily to use for calls. Sadly, everyone complained that the sound quality was mediocre and I sounded like i was on a speaker phone. Sound quality for music and calls on my end was fine, especially given the price.  I think that Bluetooth headphones are going to be inferior to a regular wired earbuds.

author: Ken Ling
title: Quality wireless ear buds
content: I had to get another pair of wireless earbuds after losing my last pair in the gym.  I wanted white this time so I went with a random brand.  I have to say sound quality on these are better than the last ones.  Instantly pairs to connect when opening the lid.  I’ve had a few gym sessions so far and haven’t had to charge the case yet (after fully charging when I first got it). Great purchase so far.

author: Erick
title: NOT A NOISE CANCEL EARBUDS
content: The built and the battery is excellent but the sound quality is not that good in my experience. These earbuds are not noise cancel and I can't feel the bass that much. When I'm outside or in the mall I can barely hear the sound even though volume is in 100% also after wearing them for a bit longer, the rook part of my ears hurt.

author: Linda Angela
title: Easily a dupe for the airpods!
content: Looks absolutely identical to the airpods! The battery life is incredible. I charge them once a week and they last all throughout the days! The only reason why I give it 4 stars instead of 5 is because the sound quality has a bit of a tinniness to it, but its very minimal. Overall, I'm very happy to have saved myself over $100 by finding these!

author: Lee
title: Exactly what I wanted
content: This is exactly what I wanted. All the features and functionality of the [Brand name] ear buds - but less than half the price. The biggest surprise was the case... it's well engineered and works intuitively with the ear buds... When you take them out of the case, they're activated and ready for use... and when you put them back in the case, they go to sleep and charge wirelessly (assuming the case is carrying a charge). Will be getting my wife a pair!

author: Elijah Daley
title: Definitely worth it
content: If I could rate this 10 stars I would. I ride a motorcycle and was looking for something I can just have in my helmet for the time being... found these and gave it a try... talking on the phone with the helmet on is amazing even when going fast.. the mic is excellent... I can whisper and still be heard... battery is amazing and the other thing I love about these is that I can either have the left one in my ear or the right in the other ear... very quick connection with auto pairing after the first pairing... I have a iPhone 7+ Just in case anyone wanted to know.

author: D.R.
title: Great and affordable!
content: Sound quality is great. It looks just like the AirPods but half the price!  The earpiece takes some getting used to, I always feel like it’s about to fall out of my ear but it hasn’t been a real issue.

author: Mo
title: Best value
content: I think this product is great for the price.  It has the traditional earbuds that stayed firmly in my ears during exercise and in my case, chores like bending over to put dishes in the dishwasher.  There is a small button on one of the earpieces that pauses and plays, which is great for when my kids interrupt me constantly.  For phone conversations, they are good but I noticed it was only 100% clear when I spoke loudly.  They’re also larger than other brands of ear pods.  Overall I’m very happy with my purchase.

author: Ritz
title: Looks close to  Airpods and great quality
content:
Amazing quality earbuds and premium material and looks shiny body  ! Sound quality is amazing and these looks closely like airpods
Has micro usb port to charge
Loving otium products purchased 2 other bluetooth headphones from them and they are great quality

author: An&Rindert
title: Bye bye annoying wires!
content:
I always wanted wireless earbuds but the Apple ones were just simply not affordable. Well good news: these are!
I can't compare the sound quality with the original ones, but I can't say anything bad about it, all my songs sound good to me. I use them to go running, since I find wires going from my ears to my pocket are very annoying and I always accidentally pull them out, or they would get strangled up in my long hair or something. It takes a bit of getting used to, but once your ears are used to them you can barely feel them! The battery life is also good, and the fact that you can just charge the case and you can put your earbuds back in the case after every use is an amazingly efficient and convenient system, so thumbs up for that!

author: Amazon Customer
title: Better than expected
content:
I received these a couple of days ago and I'm thrilled with them. They fit perfectly and don't fall out. The sound quality is decent and they can be turned up very loud. Pairing with my phone was quick and easy, though the minimal instruction manual is poorly written.

My favorite part is the case. When you open it and take the earbuds out, they automatically turn on and connect to my phone. When you put them in the case, they snap in magnetically. When you close the lid the disconnect from the phone.

I haven't yet had any problems that I've had with previous wireless earbuds such as random disconnects or one bud stopping working.

All that remains to be seen is how durable they are. My last wireless buds lasted just 3 months. These seem much better. Time will tell.

author: Mary K Low
title: Excellent value
content: Love these earbuds. I originally bought them for myself but my husband quickly took them for himself! So I bought a second set for me. We are both very happy with them. I use them in bed with my iPhone and often fall asleep with them in and am surprised by how well they stay in my ear. The sound quality is good and the Bluetooth range is excellent.

author: tx_reeg
title: Really enjoying the headphones.
content: I have really enjoyed this headphones. They connect to my phone right away and the sound quality is better than expected. The charging case that ksmicluded is really handed to store them, and that gives you that much more life from the battery. Highly recommend.

author: Priscila Parada
title: EarPods for the win!
content: I’ve been envying my friends with their EarPods, but refusing to spend $100 ! Found these only with great ratings and I am now excited to be able to hear music and such without the mess of wires. The charging pod fits perfectly within my purse and they pair specially well with Siri and iOS devices.

author: trung nguyen
title: Easy to pair and good sound
content: I've bought a few wireless headphones. This time my sister asked me for a white and 5.0 Bluetooth one. And I'm happy with this purchase. It's easily getting them connecting to her phones. And the sound quality is decent. About the look, they look great on my sister. Last but not least, it's sweatproof so I'm worried free. Highly recommend!

author: Raul Moreno
title: Awesome
content: I bought these initially because I wanted these for my work outs and I grew to love them! I can’t leave anywhere without them. They sounded great and they surprisingly good quality. They are a little bulkier than the Apple models but they have a great sporty look! It’s an awesome product and well worth the 45 bucks!

author: Paul S in AZ
title: Great value in wireless headphones.
content:
Pros:
These are a great value for truly wireless headphones.
Sound is very good
Battery lasts for hours
Works with Android 10 on Pixel 2 XL
Works with Windows 10 and google voice for calls from computer
Nice compact case that recharges the plugs
Units work by themselves, so you can charge one and continue listening with the other
Cons:
Only one size, they fit ok, but not sure if you have small ears.

author: bakerella
title: No one can hear me when I try to talk with them
content: I want to love them but unfortunately when I try to talk with my headphones on no one can hear me they say I sound like I’m either far away or they can’t hear me at all. When I listen to music it’s definitely awesome the bass is even great & they fit great in my ear.

author: WWF
title: Great earbuds, lightweight and stay in
content: I tried two other earbuds around the same price bracket before these. Both had noise cancelling silicone coverings. The first ones kept falling out; the second ones made my ears itch. I returned both. Finally I found these, which look a lot like the Apple airpods. I already have the Apple attached earphones at home for my iPhone, and I'd say the sound quality and lightness of these equal the quality of Apple earphones. This was like a Goldilocks process until I found earbuds that are just right. I have two pairs of them now--one for work and one for home. My assistant also bought them for her daughter. They're great, highly recommended.

author: Ptimewv11
title: NOT GOOD FOR HEAVY USAGE
content: Very dissapointed, Fit well, look good and decent sound quality. All is fgood as long as you dont mind having to charge the headphones after 2 o3 hours of moderate use. Battery life is horrible. I use them for a lot of calls and listening to music/podcasts. NOT GOOD FOR HEAVY USE. Everytime I get in the middle of a good pod or phone call they go dead with about a 30 second warning. Would not buy again and would not recommend.

author: Daniel Martinez
title: Good quality.
content: If you buy this expecting to get the same quality as a $180 airpods you are very mistaken. These earbuds work great so far, quality is nice and the case is awesome, sound is good, I do not like how they are sometimes not in sync when you first turn them on but after a few seconds they both play the same thing. It only has one button and it is a button, not like airpods that it is more of like a sensor. Also, you have to turn each one on manually and not just open the case and plug to start playing. Overall the sound is good but you just can't expect the same as a $180 earbuds for the price of these ones.

author: V. W.
title: Good build quality, comfortable, good audio quality, and easy pairing
content:
The T12 comes in a very nice packaging. It has a very nice carrying case that feels premium. It is a little bit bulkier than what I would have liked but it is packed with 500mAh of battery that is capable of charging the earbuds multiple times. Personally, I would not mind to have slightly smaller battery so it would make a lighter and more portable case and have a bigger battery in the earbud. So, I can use it longer than the 3.5 hours of playback time before have to recharge it.

The earbud feels well-built. It does not scream premium but does not feel cheap either. Its shape fits well in my ear and does not fall out even during light movement. It is fairly comfortable wearing it for a long period.

Pairing the device is quite easy. Re-pairing the unit is equally easy as well. I am not a huge fan that the unit stayed on for about 10 minutes after it is disconnected. While this allows the device waiting to be paired again or with another device, I just prefer to have it auto-shut off at sooner to save battery. I did encounter a couple of instances where only 1 earbud is paired to my phone and I had to turn it off and re-establish the pairing. It’s a rare event that seems to only happens when the pairing is establish with the earbud already out of the case and not when I took it out of the case (as that automatically power both earbud and establish the pairing mode).

I feel that sound quality on the T12 is very good.  The volume level is not as loud as some other headsets I have used and thus, I had to crank up the volume a tad higher. However, the earbud sounded rounded and balanced. The audio is clear and crisp. It does lack a bit of bass but I do appreciate the balanced sound.

When comes to making calls, I can hear the sound clear though I did have a few instances where the receiving end reports that the audio does not sound clear or is a bit laggy.
Disconnect the BT and re-establish the connection seems to fix the issue.

Speaking of the Bluetooth, I do feel that the BT range is not as far as some other Bluetooth.
I am also not a big fan of the hardware control as it requires you to press a button into your ear which is a bit uncomfortable. This is especially difficult when comes to double tap to skip tracks.

Couple minor things, I wish the unit can be charged with USB-C. Also, the manual seems to mixed up left and right earbud label (since the right side is the main earbud but it is labelled left side) and the text is just awfully small.

Overall, I am pretty happy with the purchase especially the sound quality. Since I use the headphone primarily for listening to music and watching movie and not as much as making calls, I enjoy using it. For its price, it offers good sound and I only wish it has longer battery life.

author: Irv
title: Learning curve not necessary.
content:
Wanting a pair of wireless earbuds but unwilling to pay Apple’s prices, let alone not knowing anything about them, I began researching alternatives on Amazon. The reviews for the vast array of options were helpful and comprehensive.
I’ve had my earbuds for about a week and so far, so good. Right out of the compact case they connected to my IPhone. The earbuds are comfortable and the sounds is great, although my listening has been limited to podcasts. I’m excited about my earbuds and hope that their value proves to support a great purchase.

author: Cece Bobbili
title: Never expected them to be really comfortable and Audio perfect
content:
I might have been a little skeptic to order.
But it definitely crossed my expectations. Priced well, for the sounds and performance.
Well fit.
Doesn’t feel uncomfortable.
Easy to answer calls with
Fast connectivity
Pretty easy to check for the led light to see if you need to charge or it has full charge.
Can use one or both and still answer calls.
Had no trouble connecting to my Samsung phone.
Haven’t tested out the battery life still. Might update with more details 👍🏻

author: Mugzie
title: Works really good except...
content: The sound quality is superb and it really last a long time before I need to actually recharge it.  love wearing this at work frees up my hands keeps me from distracting everyone else.  not sure how it compares against those apple airpods but they work as intended for me.  The only downside is that this type of earbuds just cant stay in my ear if I move too much and too fast.  My co worker tried it and it fits him perfectly and comfy!  So definitely not for every type of ears but definitely really great Bluetooth headset!

author: MiPo
title: Fit ears perfectly and tightly, case is perfectly portable
content: These headphones are the best wireless headphones that are very comparable to the branded truly wireless headphones. The connectivity on these is much better than my other truly wireless headphones, and the sound is very clear. It's great for all music lovers, movie watchers, or people who want to make calls on the run. These earphones fit very well in the ear and do not fall even when shaking your head vigorously. The charging case is beautifully made and is the best non-brand wireless headphone case I have seen. It is truly portable, as it can be placed in your back pocket. Also, the earphones have the battery life that is advertised, which is enough to last for a while. These headphones are at a great price and they're right up there with the branded headphones!

author: Derek Jang
title: Tunes for the Runner on the Go!
content:
I am an avid runner and decided to pickup these bluetooth earbuds as a spare to my normal Apple earbuds. These earbuds connected seemlessly to my ipod and the setup was very easy. I was impressed by the durability of the earbuds and the charge was quite long(seemed to last around 10 hours).

Overall I am very happy with my purchase and would recommend these earbuds to anyone looking for cheap and affordable accessory to their morning workout tunes.

author: JoAnne Young
title: Quality Earbuds
content: Very easy to pair, love the charging case too! I was surprised at the excellent quality of sound these earbuds put out! Once charged the battery lasts a long time! I bought these for my Grandson and I know he will love them!

author: tom holtslander
title: Not worth it
content: Connecting these dudes is a pain in arse. I have to remove and repair everytime I want to use them. Not worth the price

author: Gvs
title: Great product. Does the job.
content:
I’ve got this Bluetooth as a gift to my wife as this item is reasonably priced. Features are premium quality,build quality is great.
This pair of earbuds are extremely lightweight and has good battery life, the charger case is very light weight.would recommend this product in the budget.very easy to carry any where.

author: N Salam
title: My everyday companion
content: I really loved the sound quality, comparable to very expensive brand available in the market. It looks cute wearing in the ear and also very comfortable. The charge holds for really long time. The connection is super easy with both android and iOS phones. They charge in the case. The built quality is similar to other products that cost hundreds of dollars. Very happy customer

author: Balaji Ch
title: Easy to Pair n Use
content: This one is very easy to Pair and use. Good way to charge the ear phones. Ease to use is the biggest thing I liked in these ear phones. Couples of my friends thought I was using Apple Airpods and lol this one gives the same feel as the original ones. Got them for very low price. Hope these last for long.

author: Elizabeth
title: Update.
content:
Better than expected! The earbuds came in a case  and when I opened it I saw the orange light (as seen in pic). What's even cooler about this is you charge the case with the buds inside. Super sleek, feels nice, sound is decent. Well worth the money.

Update 1 week later- everything about the earbuds are great BUT it doesn't hold its charge more than  a few hours(3 to 4) before hearing the low battery warning. One day after letting it charge  overnight I ended up charging it 3 times in one day. I was aggravated compared to the other wireless I had that stays charged for days before needing charging. It ended up having a shortage and why I decided to "upgrade ". However as much as I like these headphones this is the only thing i find disappointing.

author: Aggiekrystal
title: These are fantastic!
content: I bought some other wireless earbuds recently and was sorely disappointed and ended up sending them back... so I was a bit skeptical... but these had good reviews and were reasonably priced, so I decided to give it a try... I'm so glad I did! I absolutely love these ear buds. They fit great (and I have small ears, so it's not easy to find ear buds that are comfortable). They pair easily with my iphone and hold a good charge. I have been very happy with my purchase so far. You won't regret this purchase.

author: Avik Mukherjee
title: Great Bluetooth earbud with the look and feel of an Apple earbud but 1/3rd the price
content: Its a great Bluetooth earbud with the look and feel of an Apple earbud but 1/3rd the price. I always wanted to have wireless ear pods but was not willing to spend a fortune on that. Found this one when searching in Amazon and bought it to pair with my iPhone. It got delivered fast and the product works as advertised and pairing was a breeze. Charging is through the box so minimizes the chance of loosing the earbuds. Great product and great price.

author: mmonica
title: Value buy
content: I have been using them for a couple of hours now, and I do feel happy with how they function. These are similar to airpods, but you cannot compare apples and oranges, but these are truly value for money. They fit pretty well and these can be considered a great alternative to the high end air pods. The connectivity is fast, and one other addition that I wanted to use them is because I can use them with my Android too. For the price mentioned, it is a value buy

author: Sam Cabral
title: Fooled by reviews
content: These are absolute garbage. Had them for less than a week and the sound cuts out consistently even when I'm standing still let alone working out. WARNING: DO NOT BUY.

author: Levan
title: Useless earbuds, different volume level in each earbud
content: In left earbud is high volume and in right earbud is low. I can not fix it because earbuds has no sound control. It is useless for me for listening to music.

author: Bridget R
title: Earbuds that stay put
content: I walk dogs during the day and needed something wireless. I decided to purchase these after seeing all the positive reviews. I was not disappointed! They do get quite loud. Enough that I cannot hear any of the wind or dogs barking. They do cancel out quite a bit of noise but I wouldn't say they are like a set of Bose noise cancelling headphones. Don't expect pure silence. They were easy to connect to my phone and came mostly charged. I like that the container snuggly holds the ear pieces and charges them so I don't have to worry about them going missing or run out of battery. It's nice that I can answer my phone and take calls without having to take my phone out of my pocket in the cold winter months. All in all I think they are great!

author: Vince
title: A great pair of earbuds if you don’t want AirPods
content:
I just received these today, so bear that in mind with this review.

I really love these! I was worried about buying these since a lot of other Bluetooth earbuds didn’t seem so good. But I’ve been very surprised.

The charging case is very nice, as well as the earbuds themselves. I personally think the sound is great, and they’re very light!

They were also extremely easy to pair! I was very surprised, and they pair automatically upon pulling them out of the charging case.

My one grievance is that my ears are very small, so they have a habit of falling out. I was out in my daily life for about an hour, and during that time they fell out 3 times, one at a time. I’m not sure what to do about that, but it’s nothing major for me.

I’m really glad these are good, because I really didn’t want to pay for AirPods. I might get a wrap around thing to hold the earbuds in, but otherwise they are flawless!!!

author: Amazon Customer
title: Don’t buy
content: Cracking noise in one. The other works when it wants. Junk in my experience

author: Jamison C.
title: A Major Competitor to Air Pods!!
content:
These are some impressive earbuds for the pricing! Everyone knows exactly what brand of earbud they look like and while wearing them everyone said, oh sweet you got air pods. How do you like them? Then of course when I shared with them what they were and the price they became even more intrigued.  The price and quality of these are absolutely amazing and I've already just within a week had friends order them after trying them out.
The casing is spot on and has a great feel. Just clean and simple just like the original. A big thing for me after testing many earbuds is how easy are they to get in and out of the case as some of them can be a little bit of a pain, when it should be super quick and easy. These slide in and out perfectly without any issue.
One of the nice things about these verse many others on the market is that they have the same shape and style as the air pods which is perfect for those that don't like the earbuds that go deep into the ear canal. I know many friends that complain about those types over time causing pain or discomfort to their ears, so these are fantastic for those that don't like that style of earbud.
Ultimately the sound quality is one of the most important features and now after using them for 1 week to give proper burn in and testing them against actual air pods (my wife owns a pair), these are a fantastic bang for the buck! The sound is very well balanced and I can wear them for hours without any discomfort whatsoever. They are the most comfortable earbuds I've tested to date.
If you are wanting all the features and technologies of air pods at less than a 1/3 of the price these are it. I will be buying more of these for Christmas gifts!

author: Boris Chang
title: Okay.  Not much more than that though.
content: If these really are fairly comparable to the Apple version that costs about a franklin more, then I’m glad I didn’t spend that kind of money.  I noticed a lot of people at work walking around with these in their ears.  I wasn’t sure if they were mostly listening to music or podcasts or just ready for an inbound phone call or a teleconference.  So I got this (relatively) inexpensive close.  They fall out fairly frequently (almost fell into a toilet).  And listening to music—they have almost no bass.  I’m not really surprised as the only type of earbuds that ever had great bass response had foam seals and I pushed in to seal them.  This kept the bass response good, but also made it difficult to hear outside sounds.  It probably had a higher risk of hearing damage if the volume was too high.  I don’t think you need too worry about that with these earbuds.  They just don’t stay in very well and ergo don’t sound all that great on the low end.  I can’t imagine why some of the reviewers said they had good bass response.  I respectfully disagree.

author: Vsingh93
title: Airpod-esque, but clearly different.
content:
These look very similar to airpods from a distance, but they are anything but. The case is nice and also borrows from the Airpod aesthetic, which is a good thing. It has a nice snap to it when you close it and seems to be pretty sturdy. The gloss of the case just makes it look a lot more pleasing. The case can charge the earbuds A LOT. I'm not sure exactly how much, but the case holds 500mah, and the earbuds have 30mah, so at least 8 times for the pair, and the buds last about 3hrs.

Like I said though, these are not airpods and other than the aesthetic, it's very easy to tell them apart from airpods. The ends of these are more blocky and have sharp contours as opposed to the roundness of airpods. They are also charged via micro-usb, which is a dead giveaway. They also have physical quick buttons that you can use to pause/play/pick up/end/reject calls that stand out.

The sound quality of these is really good! It's really clear when listening to music and I haven't had any issues with talking on the phone either. However, I would like to point out that (just like airpods), these don't have sound isolation. That's the trade up. You're giving that up for convenience of being able to drop them in your ear.

Connectivity is really good too. You just open the case and by the time it's in your ear, it's already connected. It disconnects after you close the case. It works in solo mode too (only using one), however you lose some functionality of the buttons.

author: Mihir Hindocha
title: Cool Earbuds
content: The first and the most important thing about having wireless earbuds is that they should fit perfectly to our ears, and I must say that these earbuds completely fulfill that requirement for me. It works really well in having phone conversations, as I do not have to yell and let everyone know what I am talking about. The quality of sound is also good and clear. Moreover, it has a good battery life which makes it an appropriate choice for me at this price.

author: Mike Speaker
title: Fit well, lightweight, good sound
content: I have used these for a few weeks now, primarily for workouts and yardwork, and I am quite happy with them.  Given the low price I found these to be a great alternative to the bigger name brands headset that looks quite similar...I am fearful of losing a much more expensive headset, so the price here is a great value without that risk, with the same functionality.  They paired easily with my iPhone, are lightweight and fit nicely in my ears (even while sweating during a workout, stayed put and are quite comfortable).  I have used a few times for 3-4 hours of consecutive music play and they held a charge during that entire time without any issues....and the sound is just as good as other small bluetooth headsets I have used.

author: J. Reamer
title: These Earbuds Work Great!
content: The packaging was very good.  Very similar to Apple packaging.  I charged the earbuds fully, while I read the instruction book let.  The instructions are straightforward with only a couple of grammar errors.  Once charged, I paired the buds to my MacBook.  Pairing was simple, as stated in the instructions.  The best part is you don't have to learn what certain beeps mean!  The earbuds tell you when the connect or loose the connection!  The sound quality is very, very good.  The ear buds seem to last quite awhile on a charge.  I have yet to run them down in a single session.  The volume is loud enough to hear while cycling on my indoor trainer which is very much appreciated!  I had to wear ear muffs over my old ones to be able to hear audio while riding.  No way to adjust volume from the buds, but I can deal with that.  I like that they can be used individually.  I forgot the left one was the Master and turned the right one off.  The left one continued to operate.  That is actually pretty cool.  I was even able to turn the right one back on.  I like the flexibility of being able to use one, or both.  The case / charger is pretty cool.  The charging light sequences as described in the manual is helpful, but will take awhile to get used to. The important thing to remember is that constant orange is fully charged.  The earbuds are magnetically pulled into the case.  They start coming back to life when you open the case, and usually connect to the MacBook shortly after I get the first one in my ear.  They are comfortable in my ears.  They stay in during indoor bike rides as well as kettlebell / bodyweight workouts!  No annoying wires to deal with.  I am 100% satisfied with my purchase!

author: Leigh Nicholson
title: You get what you pay for!
content:
"These aren't the cheapest earbuds you can buy, but you get your money's worth with these! First off, my wife is a runner and she has a hard time getting a good pair of earbuds that fit her well and sound good.Truly easy to pair, these paired up simply and easily, that isn't always the case with earbuds.
Bluetooth 5.0, this gives you longer range and more data which equals potentially better sound quailty.
Sweatproof , I would even say rain-proof. The IPX5 specification means you should be able to wear these in the rain.
Lightweight, they look big, but they don't feel big.
