Great fit, my wife returns earbuds like crazy. She is extremely picky about the comfort and feel of her earbuds. She likes these!"

author: Shiv Iyer
title: Sleek and Compact
content: A very tiny product easy to fit in your pocket. It is easy to connect and the sound quality is great. The battery was charged when shipped hence can be used right away. It is indeed a very sleek product. and performs great.

author: A. Turtenwald
title: What a great product!
content:
I just received this product last night and I love it! The sound is great and it drowns out the sounds around me.
I am using them here at work and love the fact that I work with out wires confining me as I move around my
cubicle. Set up was so easy too!

author: Kelli
title: Highly recommend
content: I bought these for my daughter who really wanted AirPods. Not wanting to spend the money on brand name, I found these. Probably the best decision!!! Literally!!!! Fit my daughters ears and connect quickly. I am very pleased that we found these! Highly recommend if you are looking for AirPods but don’t want to pay full price for them.

author: Iza
title: It works!
content:
I’m gonna start by saying that these earbuds do what they’re supposed to do and point the pros and cons next. Of course you can’t really compare to the real AirPods and i wasn’t expecting that but so far I’m liking them.

PROS:
•Great sound quality,
•Noise cancellation,
•Very lightweight,
•Easy fit in the ears,
•Easy pairing,
•Pairs right away after you remove them from the case.
•Charge lasts for a while
•Charging case
•You can activate Siri by pressing one of the buttons on it.

CONS:
•NOT good for calls, other person can’t hear you and you hear them pretty bad.
•Is not touch enabled , it has a button on each one, to skip the song and other functions.
•You can not adjust the volume on the EarPods, therefore you have to do that on you phone, which I thought it was a bummer.
•Somehow when you’re listening to music, it gets interference like it seems like the music is gonna stop or skip, scrambling the sound, which is kinda of annoying.

Overall for like a third of the price of the real one, it is not so bad and from the cons listed, the ones that annoys me the most are the calls and the volume (which you can do on your Apple Watch if you use one).

author: ThaiStick
title: Compared with Airpod, I think it is worth buying
content: I was looking for a good pair of Bluetooth/wireless earbuds. I couldn’t justified the cost of getting Apple AirPods. I saw how easy it is to loose those AirPods. So I settled on getting these pair instead. The sound quality is great for the price. The build quality is solid and they feel pretty light when you wear them. I recommend on getting a pair of these earbuds if you don’t want to spend big money on AirPods.

author: D. Gilbert
title: Great alternative to apple
content: These ear buds are really nice. The sound is very good, and they look exactly like apple airpods, but don't have that hefty price tag. You can skip songs, go back, answer calls by just pressing the button on the earbuds. I have large ears so earbuds usually don't fit me very well, but I've had these several days and they actually fit very snugly for me, which is a big plus. They fit back into a carrying case that also charges them. If you're someone who tends to lose these things, since they're so small, it doesn't make much sense to spend $200 on Apple products when these are just as good in my opinion, and a fraction of the price.

author: intlpvti
title: Unintelligable Instructions
content: The instruction "manual" may as well have been rendered in Mandarin Chinese and printed in such tiny print that you will need a magnifier.  This may well be a decent product but I have been unable to find out.

author: Kriss
title: Not good- please refund me
content: These are terrible. Poor sound, consistently unpair or just stop playing music. And they’re HUGE, barely fit in my ears. Majority of the sound issues started to occur post 30 return window. Very disappointed. Please extend my return window.

author: MS. MA XINYU
title: Good quality
content: I was initially attracted to this pair of headphones due to the similar look to AirPods. I just received them, they look basically the same and I could not tell the difference in the sound. Way cheaper and good for everyday music listening.

author: B. Homeyer
title: My earbuds arrived.
content: These are similar to the ones that are made by a popular phone company in the sense that the earpiece is not rubber. If you can handle hard plastic earbuds then you will like these. They pair with each other automatically and were very easy to pair with my android phone. The sound is very good and has a lot of bass for this type.

author: DisasterHQ
title: Nearly identical to AirPods but at a fraction of the cost
content: I love my AIrPods but sometimes it helps to have a spare set to take to the gym out when traveling. They are nearly identical to the Apple brand if you’re wearing them and you take a quick glance. I think the value is solid for the amount purchased and truly delivers as wireless ear buds compatible with Apple

author: D P
title: Very nice earbuds
content: These wireless earbuds have great sound quality, Mic also works very well. Very easy set up. I was easily able to find them on my bluetooth and it connected perfectly with ease. It has nice battery life. So far I didn't have any problem of running out of battery during a day since I charge them every night with my normal usage. They are very comfortable to wear also even if you keep them for longer hours. It is extremely good for the price. It's a great find.

author: Heather S.
title: Great ear buds for the price
content: These ear buds are great. My son loves them.  He gave 4 starts because he says they are a little big for his ears, so not the most comfortable and they fall out sometimes.  This is coming from a 12 year old boys who might have smaller ears than adults.  He did a test at school with a friend who had Apple Airpods and these ones had a better connection range.

author: Jm
title: Left stopped working
content: At first I loved these. The sound was fine (not awesome) and they stayed in place. I use them for running 3+ miles with no problems. About a month in however the left bud stopped charging and no longer works. I have to see if I can return them now because that’s not acceptable. Stinks because the price was good too.

author: Amila Porobic
title: First pair worked great- second pair absolutely horrible
content: I initially bought these a few months ago (compared to price of real AirPods) and they were great- I raved about them to all my friends. My sister forgot headphones on a recent trip so I gave her mine thinking I would buy another great set of these upon return. My new ones came in and they are absolutely horrible I’m actually shocked. So if you’re buying- be careful, quality is a hit or miss

author: Deanna shopping
title: These are good headphones
content: Nice and light way and I barely noticed that they aren't there they are nice and simplistic and I have not had any problems with them the music is good the battery is good and the feel is good

author: Unicyclebill
title: Fantastic Headphones
content: I am a drummer and I am particular when it comes to headphones but these sound fantastic and fit in my ears well.  I also like how the case lights up to indicate that the charge box has power.  I use these daily and enjoy hearing more detail in my music than I have heard before I had these.

author: Jennifer L. McClorey
title: Waste of money
content: Product work for 3 months and then the right earbud would not connect.  I got it to connect and a loud screeching noise would come out of it and no music. The left earbud worked and the right screeched.  Very disappointed that they only lasted 3 months don’t waste your money on these.  If I could return them I would.  Spend the money and get quality iPods.

author: Marcella
title: Pairs quickly with iPhone
content:
Paired these buds with my iPhone XS Max and it’s works fine. No issues. Except my ear usually end up hurting after using for some time. Happens all the time with any earbuds. They are just like apple
Wireless buds so I have no issues.

author: Kindle Customer
title: Good value for the price!!
content: my 11 year old caught these because of the price and that they looked sleek and just like Apple AirPods.  She received them today and loves them.. I don’t know if it’s selective hearing or what but they seem to cancel out outside noise. They fit her ears great and connected right away to her iPod. She’s been dancing around the room and they've stay in place so far. Seems like a great buy!

author: BrianMotz
title: Just what I needed..
content: I wanted a quality, sweatproof pair of earbuds that were quality, but moderately priced.  I was overdue for a pair as I had been using a wired pair of headsets that I'd too often have yanked out of my hears when the wires would get caught on something.  The sound on these is crisp and clear and they wear comfortably.  They are perfect for phone calls, listening to music, or one of my favorite podcasts.  Worth the money, for sure.

author: Max
title: Not bad for the price.
content:
These earbuds are not bad for the price. Sound quality isn’t spectacular but it’s acceptable for the price point. The ear buds automatically turn on once you open the case which is nice.
 The left ear bud is the master so that is the one that actually connects to your device. I did not notice any lag between earbuds and they never lost connection with each other.
One small snag that I came upon is the lack of volume control on the earbuds. This isn’t an issue with a phone or similar device but some audio transmitters do not have volume controls so these would not work in hat situation.

author: MKB
title: Great alternative to AirPods
content:
I just got these today and I’m so excited!

They pair easily. There’s a quick initial Bluetooth pairing and then every time I took them out of the case, they automatically paired with my phone.

The sound is pretty good. Nothing mind blowing, but very average to above average sound from ear buds.

Unlike AirPods, they don’t automatically pause the music when you remove a pod. And they don’t sync with Siri or anything.

I did a test call with my mom and they sound crisp and clear so they’re perfect for handsfree calling.

author: Linda
title: Lots of bang for your buck!
content:
I was surprised at the quality of sound these ear buds were! These have high quality sound & are small & super light weight. The small charging box
 That store the ear pods is perfect to slip into your pocket so you always have them. You get a LOT with the purchase of these for your money and you don’t break the bank like their Apple counter part.

author: DH
title: Good choice
content: Nice compact and cute. Love that your able to use one at a time and it doesnt turn off when you place the other in the case. Good playtime, which key when you like audiobooks. I havent tried out the option, for connecting each earbud to a seperate device.

author: Sam Adams
title: Great earbuds so far/ spoke too soon
content:
Update: 4 days later these earbuds are giving a static sound. I reset them few times but that didn’t fix it. They are going back...

Just received and tested these earbuds. Sound is great and tested with few calls. Got thumbs up from callers on the other end. I hope these last.

author: SL。214
title: Comfy, good sound quality and clear microphone
content: I have different kinds of earbuds and headphones but I have to say this is my favorite one so far.  I don’t like the in ear earbuds as they are uncomfortable after long wear and blocks out too much noise (I prefer to be able to hear my surroundings). I don’t like things on my head, naturally dislike headphones. This set is great for me! They fit well, microphone is clear and I can hear the surround just the perfect amount.

author: Katie Lembo
title: Great quality, comparable to AirPods for about 1/4 of the price.
content:
I use these at work while I do computer work and I find they have awesome sound and also are able to cancel out my nosy, annoying coworker. I also like how they don't have the cord, so no worry about leaving them around at home with the cats! Great set. I was going to splurge on AirPods but I think these do the job just fine!!

Note: I bought an AirPods silicone case to put the charging case in; it does not fit. No problem, but just in case anyone else was thinking the same thing!! Better off to use a change clutch or something!

author: Mario S.
title: Great product, excellent sound quality and noise block
content: Amazing earbuds, they are very confortable for my ears, I started using them to do exercise and they fit just right. Battery last forever and the sound quality is great, I can recommend this device to who is looking for sound block earbuds and that want to enjoy of it's favorite music without distractions.

author: Rick Perez
title: Get yours!
content: Purchased these for my 12 going on 25 year old daughter. She loves them! They paired easily and the sound quality is very good. They are noise canceling cause now she can't even hear us when we tell her to do her chores.

author: MsSuzie
title: Don't bother
content: These are horrible. Phone connection is terrible, people can't hear you. When listening to music they last maybe an hour.

author: Kallie
title: Meh...Sound goes in and out
content: Within the second use, the sound would go in and out between the headphones. I couldn’t enjoy using them as it constantly ruined the song with it stopping and skipping around.

author: Kelly
title: Good sound quality, easy to pair
content: Wow I’m so surprised by these! I have AirPods, but I wanted these as a back up pair—and let me say, they’ve exceeded my expectations. As soon as I put them in my ears, they were ready to pair. It took less than a minute to pair with my phone. Wireless quality works great and I have no complaints about the sound quality whatsoever. I’d really recommend this product!

author: Ashok
title: Great wireless ear phones
content:
These ear phones are really good, looks like airpods from far. They have crisp and clear sound. I was able to pair the ear phones easily with my iphone 7 and was able to make calls and listen to music without any issues.
It does have a good charging case to store and charge the ear phones when not in use. I like them a lot and is so much lesser than airpods.

author: O'Dalla Chen
title: The sound is good.
content: My earbuds went dead, so I decided to give the Airpods-like earbuds a try. It's amazing. The sound is good. The size is just a little bigger. The quality is great, too. It's really worth it.

author: pfolb
title: A+
content: I absolutely love it! the sound quality is crisp and the mic works well too. I use my phone a lot for work and I didn't completely believe the mic would be proficient enough. I am happy to say I was wrong. It's weighted so it doesn't feel cheap. So far so good with the battery life. I may pick up another one for my nephew.

author: AI
title: As good as more expensive Apple EarPods!
content: Very powerful EarPods that are as good as apple’s for less than half the price. Charges fast, pairs easily and has great quality sound. Absolutely a must if you are looking for EarPods or replacements!

author: Nguyen Vo
title: Great alternatives to airpods
content: Consider this pair of wireless earbuds a much cheaper and comparable quality with Apple airpods. Looks great, great sound quality, long battery life and don't hurt your ears. Great value!

author: B. DAngelo
title: Fantastic Dupes!
content: What I love the most about these earbuds is THE PRICE!  The quality and battery life is insane considering the price!  And the sweatproof technology makes it great for the gym or a heavy workout.  I would definitely recommend these, as they are easy to charge, use, and they sound fantastic!

author: Dave Huang
title: Love these wireless earbuds!
content: These TWE are great! They offer great sound quality with strong bass. The mic quality for phone is excellent! Pairing was instant as soon as they're out of the box.  Definitely recommended for anyone who wants an excellent TWE!

author: Mike Arruda
title: So glad I bought these!!
content: First I have to say that music is huge for me!! I love hearing and listening to music nap I have plenty of different headphones and ear buds. These hands down have been the best ones I have bought. You really can’t tell the difference between these and the Apple pods. The sound quality and comfortability you really can’t tell the difference and that huge. This is a great option if you are looking for a cheaper option from the Apple pods. They are fantastic!!

author: Kams
title: The first earbuds that you can feel the bass!
content: I have tried several ear buds to find the ones that I could use on a daily basis and these are so far my favorite. They fit comfortably in my ears and have a slight curve on long part of it that it does not look weird. The first earbuds where I actually felt bass in my ears. The sound is very clear and they have a solid range. Plus they sound clear to the other party when on a call. Overall they are very nice and the price is not bad either. The charging case is small and sleek so it wont take too much space. One thing I would like is that an way to turn them off without putting them back in the charging case.

author: momofkkkkk
title: Much better than expected
content: Wonderful!  They seem to just balance in the ear making them feel like they are not there.  I wear them all over the property while working and they don’t fall out.  They fit inside ear muff type hearing protectors while I’m on the tractor so I can still hear what’s playing.  Downside is the battery only lasts 4 hours before it requires a recharge.

author: Brandon
title: Good quality and comfort for a low price!
content: These feel a little bit bigger than airpods but still sound amazing and without the risk of falling out of your ears. The case fits perfectly in your pocket and is magnetic so don't worry about your earphones flying out of it. Overall a good buy!

author: Cody
title: Above average sound, average noise cancellation
content:
These wireless Bluetooth earbuds are fairly good. They fit nicely in the ear and don't feel like they are going to fall out.

When I am using them around my roommates in my loud apartment, I can hear some background noise, but most of the sound is smothered out.

The body of the earbud does feel a bit fragile, the durabilty of the plastic overtime could be questionable. But for now, they work fine.

The product works as expected and is overall an above average wireless headphones option.

author: Leah
title: Long range and easy pairing. Love them
content: I have only used these a few times yet but I am loving them so far. Easy to pair, have a long range, clear sound and great battery life! They sure are an upgrade from my last cheap earpiece!

author: WS
title: Ok buds but can’t make phone calls
content:
I’ve had these for a couple weeks and have tried them in various uses - on the subway, at the gym, running outdoors. I pair these to my iPhone 6s.

Pros: the sound quality is good and has nice bass for buds without silicon cups. They don’t cancel noise because they are not noise cancelling designed headphones (active or passive). Battery seems solid and the fit and finish are good. Pairing is fast. Comfortable.

Cons: you can’t use them to talk on the phone. When I’m on calls people can’t hear me, or it’s choppy. Basically you can’t rely on the microphone to make calls reliably. I expect the apple Bluetooth secret sauce for their brand earbuds make their brand of equipment more reliable for talking on the phone (I don’t see people with apple AirPods saying “can you hear me now?”). But these simply don’t work for phone calls. I’m that guy saying “can you hear me now” and then just stick the phone up to my ear.

They are good for listening to music, though sometimes will buzz or click as it loses signal briefly. Overall a good pair to use for exercising or listening to music because of the price, but not useful for replacing your wired headset for making phone calls.

The old adage prevails: you get what you pay for. This ain’t an AirPod 1:1 replacement.

author: jason murphy
title: Durable build. Good sound. As described. Very satisfied.
content:
Just got these today and uses them for the first time. The sound quality isnt the same as my $100 Bose but it is still really good quality and exceeds the price paid. Bluetooth paired easy.
Headphones stayed in during an intense workout of box jumps with no adjusting required.
Came fully charged and used for 2 hours and the battery still read almost full so 30h lifetime seems accurate.
Product seems very durable i was expecting it to feel cheap but it felt the same as my wifes airpods.
They are plastic and not supposed to be noise cancelling so dont know why it asked me to rate 2 things i disnt expect to get from this product.

author: Aliyah
title: Exceeded my expectations!!
content: I bought these after being unsure of whether or not I wanted to purchase AirPods. After reading all the reviews about this product, I decided to buy. These exceeded my expectations and more. I was pleasantly surprised at the sound quality, and the overall feel of the earphones in my ear! They felt very snug and even when I shook my head they didn't budge. I even let my Dad try them and he's a harsh critic when it comes to sound quality and he was amazed at the clearness and bass+treble that the earphones gave. If you're in the market for something similar to AirPods, this is what I think the next best thing!

author: D Yeung
title: Nice earbuds
content: These earbuds work pretty well. I pair them with my Samsung S10 without any problem. They are very comfortable because they just kind of hang in your ears, not really plugged into the ear canals. I can wear them for hours without any discomfort. I just wish they have more bass for music but the sound quality is just fine for the price that I paid. The charging case has a pebble shape that is quite small and light. You charge it with a micro USB cable. No wireless charging.  I am really happy about my purchase.

author: Ana E.
title: Wireless headphones
content: This wireless headphones are so good i bough they fits perfectly in my ear. They doesn’t move at all and they are comfortable. I am using them for training and they never fall off from my ear, not even if i am jumping. Battery live if really long i have used them for 3 days without charging. Sound quality is also good. This headphones are amazing specially for the price highly recommended

author: Stephen G.
title: Great headphones that stay into weird ear shapes
content: Was looking for a pair of replacement earbuds for my wife, who has 2 different ear shapes and was have some struggles keeping other buds in with replace-able ear tips. These buds seem to be a little bit less flexible in their design, but do a great job at staying in the ear! They don't move around or shift and the longer shaft leading down really seems to stabilize them in the ear. Recommend you give them a try!

author: mahael1
title: Great Earpods for the price!
content: I bought a variety of pairs to test them out because my kids will gladly take the others I don't want. These are seriously one of the best pairs I bought. Great sound quality, decently comfortable, and extremely light. I haven't yet had a chance to test the moisture-wicking aspect, as I'm not a guy that wears them while working out, swimming, etc, however, I will say there are decently loud, comfortable, and have a respectable bass for earpods. I do believe these are my winners out of multiple pairs that I have purchased!

author: Maria urrutia
title: Just like airpods
content: Being using them for a little less then a week and I’m in love.. baterry last such a good time then the fact the case you can charge them again I honestly do reccoment them!! They worth every penny. The sounds is actually good as well

author: C. McKenzie
title: Worked great for 3 weeks and then stopped, and the plastic is melted
content: These worked great until today (about 3 weeks).  The right ear was not working and after reviewing closely, the plastic has melted on the stem.  Since they were in the charger, I assuming something has gone wrong with the lithium battery and overheated.  It is hard to see in the picture, but just below the earbud, the plastic melted on the stem.

author: Ingkawat
title: Amazing EarPods with affordable price!
content: It's my first EarPods, and I was satisfied, and loved it. It comes in beautiful and modern design, and has light weight. It has good sound quality and noise cancelling. It also comes with charging case. It connects and works with my phone very well. The overall quality if the product is very good with reasonable price. Worth the money!!

author: Cheriss
title: So convenient
content: This is my first set of wireless ear buds and it is SO convenient not to have wires everywhere! I’ve found them to be a little big and slightly uncomfortable for my ears unless I get them adjusted just right, but I have very small ears. Sound quality is good and they are very easy to set up, charge, and use.

author: Raquel
title: Too big! have to be constantly adjusting them so they don’t fall even walking
content:
The earbuds are too big, they don’t stay in my ears.. I have to be constantly adjusting them so they won’t fall.  I’m afraid to use them while riding my bicycle or running because of that. I wanted wireless earbuds so I could exercise without having to worry about the cable of regular earphones getting stuck. But this earphones I can’t even use them if I’m walking. It happened twice that I was just walking and one of them felt. Even if I am at the office  desk sitting, but just turning my head to talk to my coworker, i feel how they are about to feel so I have to adjust them every 2 min.
The sound quality is okay (not like iPods) and it works for calls. However, it also happens that once in a while the sound stops or pauses for like 2-3 seconds. I reset them and te problem is fixed but is also annoying to reset them when you expect sound clarity all the time. I think that for these reasons the price should be lower. Definitely didn’t meet my expectations for almost $50.

author: Hoodschwinked
title: Nice buds!
content: These are nice! I’ve never had AirPods. But I’ve used Bose headphones. And the quality is very good here. I personally did not like them bc I have freakishly small ears. So they were never secure. Of course my family loves them now lol and everyone thinks my 11yo has real AirPods 😂 NOT!

author: roatkins
title: Very Nice High Quality Wireless Earbuds
content:
I ordered this pair of earbuds because I had always wanted a pair like them, but I did not want to pay over $100 dollars for a pair. I took a chance and ordered these based off the reviews, price and quality of the product and it’s features.
When I received them I opened the box and right away I was very impressed with the quality of the build and how the wireless earbuds were packaged.
They came with everything listed in the item description on Amazon. I took them out of their charger case and they immediately went into pairing mode. I was very impressed with the speed of which these wireless earbuds paired to my iPhone.
More impressive is the quality of the sound they have. Music is very clear and I was able to go from soft to very loud without distortion. You can be heard clearly when you are on them. They are lite weight and you hardly know you have them on.
If you are in the market for a new set of wireless earbuds and ones that are very well made, I highly recommend them to you.
As always when purchasing a product via Amazon Prime you always have they return policy there for any issues.
I hope you enjoy them as much as I do.

author: Lee
title: Looks nice, sounds nice, priced nicely
content: Good quality and solid material. Very nice and smooth looking. Fits comfortably in ears and is lightweight and balanced. Sound quality is good and gets loud enough. Easy to pair and battery lasts about 4 hours listening or using. Charges in a snap with magnetic charger and carry case. Great value for a quality earbud.

author: SH
title: The Battery life quoted is not true in real life
content:
The unit is quick to connect. sounds about the same as Airpods. Also shows the battery life in widgets on the iPhone.
But biggest let down is the battery life is not close to what is advertised or claimed. Left side unit drained out faster. I checked the widget , it said 70% battery life left. But the left side unit was saying to charge the unit as its low on charge.This happened after 2 hours of usage. I have been using this for couple of days now..

Thinking of returning the unit as this is BIG LET DOWN and seller is not true to what they advertise.

author: SURESH KUMAR SAH
title: Awesome Quality at Great Price
content:
I was thoroughly impressed with the headphones. The packaging was incredible, the quality is top notch, and an amazing set of features for the price even if the price was twice as high. Wireless charging, IPX8 waterproofing, high quality sound and bluetooth v5.0 are just a few of the high end features this earbud have to offer.

Pairing them with my phone was too easy. All you have to do is take them out of the charging case and they are ready for pairing( just a quick note make sure you choose T10, the right earbud is the primary). The bluetooth v5.0 mean they have a stronger connection and longer distance. I can leave them in my backpack and I am still connected up to 30 feet away. The clarity of the highs and the richness of the bass are of the quality level of the highest end earbuds. I was pleasantly surprised to find that I could use my T10s for a little over four hours and the charging case is good for four full recharges of the earbuds. Finally, I have to say the  chargeable case is very handy. All in all for the price I could not find a better earbud on the market.

author: Chris1calico
title: Sound and comfort
content:
I'm surprised for the value the kind of  quality  with this earbuds, crystal clear sound and since I dont have my phone on me all the time, I can leave and literally walk around my entire house without losing connectivity!
Battery is length is at 5hours.

author: Jayy Z
title: Amazing earbuds. Totally worth the buy
content:
If you are looking for a decently priced but insanely good earbuds then you should really gives these bad-boys a try. The design is nice and smooth and seems to fit in my ear perfectly. Doesn’t come off either.
The material used is really good as well as the earbuds don’t seem cheap or third-rated.
The sound quality is surprisingly good. Gets really loud but doesn’t distort the music in any shape or form.
The connectivity is easily the best part about these. They seem to connect so smoothly and easily. You just open up the case and put them in your ear. You’ll hear the ‘connected’ sound and voila. I’m honestly amazed on how quickly these connect.

author: Jessie & Ed
title: Great earphones!
content:
If you're looking for good earphones for both listening to music as well as making calls, these would be it!
Pairing: super easy, literally just one click on phone.
Sound: The sound is well balanced, and is very clear even at high volumes. The mid and highs are recreated well. Overall, I love the output and there isn't any lag between the earphones.
Charge/Power: It seems to be getting the advertised 5-6 hours of runtime and the charger is quick.
Microphone: Phone calls are good if not a little faint.
Fit and Finish: the case and the build quality of the headphones is great! No gap in the case. The magnets hold the headphones into the case securely. The case is really nice and small, easy to put anywhere.
Sport/Waterproof: I have tested this twice on 5k run, the buds stayed there very nicely the whole time.
This pair has fast become one of my favorites. They look like the AirPods in appearance, but are several notches lower in price. The product is well documented, and the quick start guide is mostly all you need. Can’t say anything bad!

author: Wesley
title: Great Product for a Great Price
content: These earbuds were delivered today and I was able to charge and use them for about 3 hours. Sound is great. Though even while working at a desk they did fall out a few times so I don't think they would do well while working out. I went with these because the price is too good to beat and the reviews were very positive.

author: Dennis
title: Headphone is well worth the cost, but the battery is limited
content: The pods worked really well, the quality is amazing, they don't fall out and they easily connect through bluetooth. One down fall I would say is that you would have to refer to the user manual to understand the charges left in the case, and that the pods seem to have a quickly decaying battery after several charges (still lasts around 2-3 hours, but not the advertised 5 hours).

author: sk
title: Great inexpensive alternative to airpods!
content: Great earbuds! I said inexpensive, not cheap, as they dont cost a lot, but seem very high quality.  Connect via micro usb on bottom, which is convenient, since it's near universal, has a status light on the bottom, and the earbud case is slightly magnetized to keep tje buds captured and secure for charging.  Buds themselves have a nicely designed button for paring/actions. Large enough to find easily, but low profile enough to not look silly. Overall very, very pleased with these!

author: Eloisa
title: Decent given the price.
content:
Actually not a bad product. Sound quality was surprisingly good compared to other wireless earbuds at this around this price, and pairing is super quick after opening the case (I have a Galaxy S10+).

I'm a small person and the buds themselves were a bit large, but didnt cause too much discomfort. Though I did feel fatigue after wearing them for more than an hour, so thats something to note. During the 1-2 hours I would wear them for, I did notice them getting uncomfortably warm in my ears.

But, since getting them, I havent needed to charge them. I used them for maybe 4 hours per day since I've gotten them and havent needed to charge the case yet, so battery life is pretty good.

Having the physical buttons however does feel pretty clunky, and weird especially hearing the click in your ears when you press it (it also presses into your ear more when you so this).

As for the case, it feels pretty heavy and well made. I own the i10ws as well, and the quality compared to that is far better. The hinge does worry me as it feels a bit loose, but overall, its pretty good and I wouldnt worry about it breaking unless I smacked the top part of the case with a good amount of force.

TLDR; Good for the price. Build quality is great. Not good for people with smaller ear openings. Quick pairing.

Pros:
- Small & easy to carry around
- Good battery life
- Good sound (bass is more prominent than the treble though, mids seem kind of drowned out, but can easily be fixed with an equalizer)
- Decent case build.

Cons:
- Gets worryingly warm after about an hour of use.
- Buds on the larger side. Causes fatigue after wearing them for a while.
- Buttons require a decent amount of force to press (causing discomfort) but function as advertised.

author: KG
title: Quality earbuds at a fraction of the price!
content: To be honest, I was quite wary about these earbuds when I initially purchased them, but I needed a cheap set of earbuds fast, so I decided to take a chance with these. Boy was I surprised. First off, the sound quality of these are pretty good. They are comparable to the Apple AirPods, but they lose slightly. Main difference between the sound is the bass; these do not have as much, which could be good or bad depending on your preference. These also are not fitted like the AirPods, so they may not fit as well or snug. But despite these "issues," these earbuds are still a good deal at the price they are at. They charge for a short amount of time and usually hold around six hours for me. Overall, a good pair of earbuds that I happily recommend.

author: Wendy
title: Valuable earbuds!
content:
It works for very long time, more than 4 hours when I first got it without any charge. And it can connect with my laptop in about 20meters, I can listen to the drama while I'm cooking in the kitchen, that's really cool!
Most important, when I wear it to wash face, it drop off into the water, I was scared, but pick up, and press the play button, it works as usual! Thanks for the waterproof! lol

author: apotty
title: Nice comfortable earbuds
content:
These earbuds are pretty nice, comfortable and the sound quality is great.
It is easy to set up and the battery seems to last 6-7 hours which is extremely good for the price.
The case is nice.

author: James B
title: Very nice earbuds
content:
Received this product very quickly as I requested no rush shipping. It paired flawlessly with my iPhone 7. Sound was surprisingly excellent.  Just a tip on pairing - go to settings menu and bluetooth. T12 is discovered and click to pair. This is different for users of Apple brand earbuds as it is discovered on your home screen and you don't need to go to the settings menu. Not sure about pairing with new iPhone 11. Suggest you ask the seller if it compatible. I have seen comments on other wireless earbuds stating not compatible with iPhone 11 due to the new chip Apple uses in these iPhones.
Fits well in both ears. It had a Transparency code on the box that verified my ear buds with the manufactured specs and authenticity.
I will update if any issues arise over time. Hope this helps potential buyers of this product.

author: Lis
title: Very practical
content: Good pair of wireless earbuds. They are waterproof. The charging case is so small and practical to take everywhere. The case  is durable and handy. Nice magnet closing. Works well,  sounds are Great wearing with music block outside noise.

author: Amazon Customer
title: These work great
content: I use headsets and earbuds all day long and these work fantastic.  Will they do noise cancelling on a flight with a screaming baby?  NO.  They are earbuds and not giant over the ear headphones.  They turn on when you open the case and connect instantly to your phone or whatever and work.  These just flat out work, i use them primarily for webex stuff and walking through the airport.  I do use my over the ear giant headphones for drowning out the screaming babies on flights, these do the job in between all that.  They have no problem connecting to my google Pixel or Macbook pro.  I constantly lose headsets or leave them in hotels or rental cars and try to keep the budget low.  These work fantastic.

author: charles wu
title: nice 3rd party airpods
content: this earbud looks like apple airpod but it's not airpods. the headphone has a pretty good bass output, sound quality is also great. for normal use is perfect. but because it looks like airpods style, the noise canceling is not as great (apple airpod also has not good noise canceling). the battery is ok, it has around 5 hours lifetime.

author: Pete
title: Surprisingly great
content: It should be no secret what these earbuds are trying to emulate, and if you choose to go with these, you’ll be highly satisfied with your purchase. The binaural sounds these can create are unreal they definitely take advantage of both speakers on each earbud. Touch controls work great and listening to music is like a new experience with these, money well spent on these

author: Upstate fire
title: Wife loves them!
content: Bought these for my wife, she needs this style as the stubby ones (technical term) don't stay in her ear very well.  These have been great so far (1 week). No issues connecting, good sound and decent distance.  Very pleasantly surprised.

author: Amazon Customer
title: Not the right product for me
content: I’m used to a regular hook over the ear Bluetooth device but I wanted to try something new. For me, this isn’t a great fit. I work outside and these didn’t stay in ear during work. These earbuds fell out constantly. I am not impressed and wish I didn’t make the purchase. This is just me though. When a call comes in only the number is announced and not the name. I didn’t like that. As for me I will stick to my plantronics over the ear Bluetooth.

author: Sandra B
title: Impressed with the quality
content: I am so impressed with the excellent sound quality of this earbuds. They are like apple earbuds, SO comfortable to wear, stable in your ears and the battery lasts long. I have used them in calls and video calls and people says they hear me perfectly

author: Brandon L. Moore
title: These earphones don't disappoint
content: These earphones are now my top choice. I have several other models, but these are now my go-to for their comfort and superb audio quality. Battery life is great too. The earphones have a solid build quality and the charging case is compact and convenient to throw in my pocket or bag.

author: Jamal G
title: Wow these earbuds are comfortable!
content:
These rademax bluetooth earbuds are very comfortable and feel like the ones that come with the iPhone.

Sound quality is good, I love not having cables running to my phone:)

Battery life is great, and they pair every time I take them out of the case.

I highly recommend them for the price!

author: Scully
title: Comfy and great charging!
content:
I love this product. It charges my earphones fairly quickly and is so durable when I just want to toss it really quickly into my bag when I'm in a rush to leave.

The case is really great! The USB cable connects the case charger to charge the earphones. I've had issues in the past with other brands where I wake up and realize my earphones were not fully charged thanks to it not being properly put in the dock. With this, it fits snugly and I don't have to worry about it not charging for the next day. Best thing is the LED lights let you know when the case is fully charged and how much battery is left to charge the next time.

For me, this is good enough, but the most important thing is that it is comfortable and has a stable wear. I have a problem with my right ear, where it won't fit and any earphone I try, it will fall off. But I have no problem with this earphone set. I'm glad I found the right product for myself.

author: Ahmed Asif
title: Comparable sound quality to Airpod
content: I was surprised with this Bluetooth’s sound quality. Good bass and treble. I bought many pairs from amazon previously but this earbud is awesome. Good quality. Within one charge it stays alive more than seven to eight hours. Loved those.

author: AW
title: Do not work consistently
content: When these work, they're fine. However, they don't work on a consistent basis. Even when I'm just sitting at my computer watching a webinar or movie they keep disconnecting and reconnecting on their own. There is also a static noise in the left ear that I can hear over everything and sometimes a high pitched screeching that's really annoying. I bought these to use while on calls with clients for work and I can see after using them a handful of times that they're not good quality so I'll be returning them, unfortunately.

author: Michelle Riffle
title: Ok replacement for airpods
content: I needed an extra pair of these for my boyfriend and I and they work well, good sound quality and you couldn’t tell they’re not AirPods unless you looked really hard! I love the look of them

author: N. Ng
title: Not ideal for music playback
content: These are adequately good only for phone calls. These earbuds also lack funtions to increase volume and skip tracks. If you're planning to use them from in a loud environment such as gym, concert, or party, forget it.

author: Bill M. Vane
title: Amazing! :)
content: I am not one that will spend the 100+ dollars on the Apple ear pods. I was hoping these would do the job and BOY do they ever. They sound amazing and fit in my ear perfect and have not fell out! Do yourself a favor and grab some of these before they are gone.

author: iSatisfied
title: Great alternative to the apple airpods!
content: Ever since I upgraded to iphone XS, I was looking for a good set of wireless bluetooth headphones to carry around so I wouldn't have to carry my phone all the time.  The apple airpods were nice but they cost nearly $200.  I decided to give these a try since it was a fraction of the price, and it has been amazing! Pairing with the phone was very instant and easy and It connects to the phone right away.  Sound quality is great; I can hear my wife very clearly when I drive and she can hear me without a lot of outside noises.  Battery life is good about 6-7 hrs.  It is lightweight and comes in a similar box as the airpods, which makes it easy to carry around.  It comes with its instructions on how to receive and ignore the call from the earbud itself as well.  If you are looking for a good set of earbuds but don't want to overpay, get these earbuds for similar quality but for a lot lot less!

author: BrandonG777
title: My best set of bluetooth headphones thus far
content: I own a few different sets of bluetooth headphones and these are the best of them. Sound quality is surprisingly good and these are actually the most comfortable. My others have the rubber ear pieces but these just hard plastic and are actually more comfortable in my ear. Real buttons to pause/play is a huge plus, some of my others have touch controls which I accidentally hit when I adjust them. Some of my other headsets also feature a battery guage on the case which is convenient but I can tell the charge level of the headphones on my phone (tested on both iPhone 13 and Android 10). Highly recommend.

author: Ashley Gould
title: Good balanced sound earbuds
content:
The sound is great. It's a very good balanced sound and it is clear enough to hear any imperfections in our digital music. I'm a music guy, so sound quality is important to me. I gave it a 5/5 stars but temper your expectations. I found it to have more than enough bass, and mids and highs were crisp and detailed. I gave it 5/5 as I'm comparing it against other wireless bluetooth earbuds.
 It also cancels noise because it plugs your ear canal. That's it. These should even have a noise cancellation rating as I think that should be reserved strictly for Active Noise Cancellation.

author: mlewis52
title: Consider me impressed
content: So far so good with these earbuds - these obviously look like the AirPods but surprisingly function and operate like them too. I’m impressed with the sound quality and comfort and look forward to many hours of listening to music with these bad boys!

author: LL
title: Garbage
content:
cheap quality
item delivered without any kind of proper wrapping.
sound delay between left and right side.
random choppy connection when moving

author: Oscar Lee
title: Awesome earbuds
content: Works really well. Pairs almost instantaneously. Sound and microphone are clear. Earbuds and case both well made. Case is magnetic, bigger than normal air pod case but also holds more power. The earbuds work well when I walk away from my phone too. Overall great. Only thing missing is the in ear sensor.

author: Salem
title: Quality audio and comfortable fit
content:
I was very impressed by these earbuds. These are really nice and portable earpod imitations of other more expensive pods but with high quality audio. They are a comfortable fit in the ear and the battery life lasts a long time. You charge them through the carrying case and it's all magnetic so you won't lose them. They automatically power off in the case so the charge lasts a long time.

They're very simple to use and connect to via bluetooth. I was surprised by the built in microphone which worked really well on a call I used them for. The multifunction can answer calls, end calls, and reject calls and it switches right back to music when the call is over. If you have an Apple device, you can activate Siri using the multifunction button so they're just like the name brand ones. The hardest part is memorizing the functions of the multifunction button.

author: Dany Boy
title: Similar to real ones!
content:
I recently got a new iPhone and paid extra for the headphones. After I came across this I decided to give it a shot to see if it's similar to my wireless headphones. I can honestly say that I could've saved a lot more money going with this!

I like the design for a few reasons!

1. Similar to Airpods literally!
2. Comes in it's own secure case!
3. Charge lasts long

I can't complain about a good product especially when the price is right! Overall I would give this product 5 stars for my experience!

author: Jerro
title: Disappointed
content:
This product connected easily to my apple devices, but the sound quality was poor, with no depth in the music. Telephone conversations were a disaster, the person on the other end of the call could hardly hear me, even though I could hear them just fine. Eventually stopped using them for calls. Not a good buy. feel I've wasted my money.

I am updating my experience by one star for now.  After my unhappy post, the seller reached out to me and offered a replacement set of earphones of a different type.  I thought this was a very good gesture and shows a sincere desire to have satisfied and happy customers.  I am indeed appreciative of this gesture.  I now await the arrival of the new earphones to see if the quality of the product improves.  Stay tuned.

So.. I received a complimentary pair of conoco earbuds, to replace the pair I was unhappy with. The new pair is much better both in design and sound quality. Sound quality is excellent both for music and conversations. I love these. 4 stars.

author: Noah Hanks
title: Great value compared to airpods
content: These things fit into your ear just like regular apple airpods and feel great. They connect pretty easily to your phone and have great audio quality. I'd recommend this for anyone who wants wireless audio but doesn't want to spend hundreds

author: Johnny Adam
title: Just as good as the expensive stuff. Try them!
content: Excellent audio response. Just as good as AirPods that I've tried. Getting about 3 hours run time in stereo mode. Happy with that because the “fruit” version doesn't do much better than that. Made a few phone calls, person on the other end had no issues with my audio. They charge to 100% real fast, so down time is minimal. Looking forward to getting more of these.

author: M07
title: Very Good for the price paid
content:
Overall this earbuds are good
Sound is  good compared to other wireless earbuds
Mic works good.
Easy to pair to your phone
Automatically connects to your phone (iphone ) in my case
Not cheap quality material

author: Peggy
title: High quality sound earbuds are good for couple and exceriser
content: These Bluetooth earbuds are amazing and better than  any other earbuds I have used before. It can be worn when you exercise and it won’t be fall. Its sound is similar to AirPod and price is reasonable and affordable for me. According to my good experience, my boyfriend bought another one to try it. It is a really good so I recommend it.

author: Mercedes
title: Earbuds
content: I find these buds fit OKAY!  After awhile they do tend to come out of the ear.  Sound quality is NOT that great.. especially when outside..the Volume quality goes weak....even on a full charge!  If you looking for a high, Professional quality ear buds, I don not  recommend!

author: Lei W.
title: Good pair of wireless earbuds
content: I have been searching for a set of wireless earbuds that will stay in my ears. I have tried ones with the soft tips but they usually slip out of my ears, even trying all the tip sizes. These partial-in-ear earbuds fit comfortably and more importantly, did not fall out when I jumped up and down and went about my day. The sound quality is pretty good though I have not tried to listen to music in a loud/busy environment yet. One slightly inconvenient point is the lack of volume control on the earbuds themselves -- I would need to adjust the volume from my phone/computer, etc. Pairing to my Android phone required a minute or two for the earbuds to be detected and upon first detection, the volume is at maximum so make sure to not have the earbuds in your ears when you pair them for the first time to a device.

author: Nathan O
title: Extremely pleased
content: Bought this for my girlfriend's birthday and she loves them! They look and feel just much like airpods which is not what I was expecting.  They are much better than my generic brand bluetooth wireless earbuds I just bought for myself, the case is much more compact and putting them in to charge feels much more intuitive and less clunky than mine does. My girlfriend is happy and so am I. Next thing she needs is a cute decal for the case. I wonder if ones designed for airpods would fit this?

author: Thejo Thomas
title: Cute !!!!
content: Very easy to connect, so convenient and also good sound quality, comfortable and they do stay in ear well. I had several people try them, and most people found them to be comfortable. This product is seems like iPods.

author: Rindie C
title: I like these a lot
content: I've been in search of the perfect wireless headphones that fit well in the ears and don't cost an arm and a leg. These work very well. I listen mostly to spoken word with headphones on and they are great for that, but also good enough forlistening to  music from the phone or computer.

author: gary reeves
title: A good design, and small portable charging unit.
content: Everyone gets me to find headset for them,as per example My brother rob was looking for a pair such as these , comfortable compact and portable charging that can fit in his pocket. A lovely design as well.

author: LeslieP
title: Exactly what I was looking for
content: I was looking for a pair of bluetooth ear buds for my iPod to use while working out. The earbuds were delivered quickly. They connected to my iPod in second and the sound quality is very good. I didn't want to spend $100+ on a pair of Apple airbuds. A very good value.

author: Sara A
title: Very cheap, low-quality earphones.
content:
The left ear pod stopped working at three weeks. Couldn't talk on the phone without other person saying I sounded warbled. Very, very cheap headphones. Do not waste your money.

Only plus is that they fit comfortabley and the battery life isn't completely terrible.

author: Travis
title: Great design with great sound!
content: I really like these earbuds. They stay in my ears surprisingly well and have great sound. They were easy to connect and offer great battery life. The magnetic design of the case is also really cool. They just snap into place.

author: shane fadden
title: Better than I thought!
content: I just got these in so this is a review of only having them today. They seem like good quality. The charger is very functional and they connect instantly when pulled from the case. The sound quality is actually pretty good! Nice and loud. I was not expecting this. They are pretty comfortable, a little big but not bad. Very light and stay in place. I’m overall impressed. I bought these for the gym and they’ll be perfect.

author: Sam
title: Good alternative to the apple airpods
content: I was hesitating to use any other brand then apple airpods. But it's been over a week and it's working good. They are pretty easy to connect. Voice quality also good. works with apple & Android both. Battery life is pretty good. Fitting is also good no issue so far. it also convenient and easy to travel with. Case is nice & compact. Earbuds comes with charging cable. You can give it a try.

author: Anand
title: Perfect replacement for AirPods
content:
This earbuds are perfectly fit in my ears and sound quality is superb. I have used this earbuds for more than 1 hours continuously  but don’t feel pain in ears. Battery last long and would say perfect replacement for AirPods if u looks for cheep and best option.

Pairing is not a big deals where i have used other earphones that need to turn on everytime and turn off manually but this one is hassle free just take out and put it back in the box.

On the whole it’s really cool one for sure and you won’t regret after buying...

author: Daisy
title: Great value of money and good sound quality
content: This earbuds is very stylish and light to carry. Also the sound quality is great and also comes with microphone. The box is able to let me charge my earbuds wherever I go. Though compared to the bug brand one, they are not exactly the same; but taking price into consideration, this one is a great value of money.

author: Arinjoy
title: Loud and clear bluetooth earbuds.
content:
I wanted to try out new earpods which I didn't have to charge too much, this was the perfect one I think there is in the market.

Here are my thoughts regarding the whole product as a whole :

SIZE/FIT : These earpods fit perfectly in my ear, and due to the matte finish it has an awesome grip to it. The case is the correct size and it feels robust. Without sacrificing the size, it packed a lot of battery.

BATTERY LIFE : I can easily go on continuously listening to songs for 2 days straight. Obviously though it is slow charging of my google pixel xl. But it helps as you don't have carry any extra power bank with you.

SOUND QUALITY : As I mentioned in my headline, this earpod is mostly awesome for its bass. It packs a punch and the sound quality is through the roof (as per the money paid).

CONNECTIVITY : Bluetooth range is about 5-10 meters and it is really easy to connect to my android device. It also shows the charger percentage beside the connected earpod (like an airpod shows for apple devices).

COMFORT : I like these earbuds fit flush into my ears unlike other outward-looking earbuds. It fits snugly with the standard rubber buds, and I can barely feel they are on my ears after 30 minutes. I have a problem that I can't wear over the ear headphones, there are a perfect choice for me since it doesn't make my ears hot or red after a while.

Overall I think it is a great value for money even though it might look as if $45 is too much. Worth it, 100%.

author: Saad
title: All the same features as AirPods for a fraction of the cost.
content: Very comparable to Apple's $150 AirPods. For a fraction of the price these are a very decent alternative if you're trying to save around $100. All the same functions, this has a small button instead of touch sensitive controls. I recommend these for the price.

author: Aswinkumar
title: Small, Cute, Fits Snug, Awesome Sound!
content:
Absolute Stunner. The first thing that you would notice about this when you open the package is its small form factor and stunning quality. The box is very "small" and "cute".

Functionality: More than what meets the eye, stunning quality that is as good as name-branded ones. I ve tried listening to rock, jazz, and tonnes of calls - PERFECT.

I will definitely recommend this to everyone.

author: NICKM38
title: I’m impressed
content:
These earbuds are slightly larger than the brand name ones, so if you have small ears they may not be a fit for you, I have normal size ears and they fit and stay in place well.
 The material both for the case charger and earbuds is top quality. The sound is equal or better than the high end  expensive ones.
I bought these as a gift and after testing them I am buying an extra set for my personal use. Can’t beat the quality and sound for such an inexpensive set of wireless earbuds. My suggestion: buy, buy, buy, you will love them.

author: NN786
title: Great Bluetooth headphones!
content: My husband loves these. He wanted the air pods but because of the price we decided to go with these instead. The sound quality is great and of course the price is perfect!

author: Mit Desai
title: Well made, good sound
content:
I really like the sound quality. This are finally the wireless earbuds that doesn't fall from my ear. Nice quality material and well made.

They do derive the design from airpods but had some differences. Mainly the part that sticks out of the ear is a bit larger than airpods

author: Om Tripathi
title: Very nice ear buds
content: Its really nice and I save lot of Dollars by this purchase, because it works with iPhone as well. I was thinking I would need to buy Apple earbuds but this one is equally good and fit to my ear. Loving it. Superb deal.

author: CW
title: Good quality
content: I tried it to listen to YouTube while working out. The sound is clear, good quality. The pair to my phone has no problem. It also has voice messages when the blue tooth is connected and disconnected. I like the size and color, too.

author: ana
title: Stopped working after 2.5 weeks
content: I genuinely don't know if all the positive reviews are real. I wanted to like these, the charging case is adorable and definitely looks like the airpods. I didn't even have them for 3 weeks before the left ear bud completely stopped working! And when they did work they quality wasn't amazing, I could accept it but they definitely were not great during exercises, I had to take them out and dry them a few times so they would stop from slipping due to sweat. Honestly if you are in doubt of getting them then listen to your gut, this company needs to fix a lot of things to make these buds worth 45 bucks.

author: patrick hoang
title: Affordable
content: I've been meaning to get wireless earbuds for a while now since I hit the gym a lot. I've always used the old fashion wired ones, but I get tired of them since always do running, the wire always dangles and gets unplugged. So I came across these on Amazon! I mean for the price we're paying, way more affordable than Airpods. Sound quality isn't bad either. I did like how fast the customer service was when I told them the first one they sent me had a defect on it and they got back to me instantly. One thing I like and notice about these are when you remove one of the earbuds, the other one still plays. I know when you do this for Airpods, the other earbud still in your ear instantly stops playing music. Overall worth the price and the customer service was very responsive.

author: Nicholas Sparagis
title: Impressive
content:
So, I these are essentially a clone of the Airpods.  For the cost, it's pretty amazing what they were able to accomplish.  The fit well, great sound and the call quality is excellent.  The subtle differences is that they are slightly larger, in the ear and protruding out.  This is week one, so let's see how long they last.  If I get a year + out of these 5 stars all the way.

***Update***
Still impressed with these, but the battery life is not good.  It's less than 2 hours :0

author: Chill Bill
title: Good sound quality
content: These ear phones are a good buy at the given price. It has good sound quality and fits in the ear quite well. It also looks very much similar to the apple airpods but are much cheaper.  It was easily paired with my iphone-X and has good range coverage.

author: Dezertfox
title: Closest to airpods I have tried yet
content: After losing a couple of airpods I did not want to spend another 150$ on earpods. I have tried different designs but none of them had the airpod fit for me. These come the closest with pretty good sound quality and I can use it during my walks or workouts and they don't fall out. It's still a little big for my ears but mine are on the smaller side so for most people it should be fine imo.

author: KL
title: Great earbud!
content: Incredible sound quality.  I had the original from apple, but when I lost it, didn't want to buy another one at the ridiculous price.  Price is really good for this earbud, but the sound is even better.  Can't go wrong with this one.

author: Amazon Customer
title: Impressed, would gift it to someone
content: Came nicely packaged, connecting for the first time was easy and quick. I like that you don't have to wait for these to turn on, then connect unlike my previous earphones. The sound quality is great, good bass and clarity. The equilizer can be adjusted in in most app so I set it accordingly. The fit is comfortable for my ears. For smaller ear cannals, the ear peice might stick out a bit. These fit my ears better than the apple airpods. The case iis durabale and  has magnetic cover so very easy and quick to open. The call sound is decent, not the crispiest, but the otherperson can understand well. Overall, great product and its great for listening music, audiobooks and making calls.

author: JW
title: great product for a great price. work well.
content: these have a really nice fit and the magnetic closure of the charging case is great. they connect easily and have not had any disconnecting issues. the sound is good but i wouldnt call it great. if you dont have an "ear" for music then these will be perfect. The charge lasts quite a long time. they  stay in well when working out or playing sports.

author: Amazon Customer
title: Issues
content: Returned the first earbud for fading in and out of one earbud.  They sent me a replacement and the side button would not work for turning on and off or anything else.  I really hated that product didn’t work because the sound quality was fine.

author: Unkle Cleo
title: maybe not so good
content:
arrived a day early and was quite excited to pair these with my iPhone 5SE.  Sound quality was decent, but not nearly as rich or full-bodied as my apple corded ear buds.
there is no volume control on the buds, it must be done on the device.  kind of a nuisance really.  if my phone is pocketed, and i want to change the volume, i have to pull the phone from the pocket - that defeats the purpose of being hands-free.
also, the body is a little larger than the apple version resulting in a fit not quite as good as the apple.
what's more, there is no device memory on these buds.  each time you change devices you must re-pair the buds to the device.  these buds do not remember all of the devices to which they were paired, only the last one, which is another defeat of the wireless idea.
another downside is the fact they provided all kinds of static on my macbook, but not on my iPhone.  don't understand that.
so, with all the less-than-ideal characteristics of these buds, i returned mine.  too bad too, i really wanted to use these.

author: Mrunal Shah
title: Great product for the price
content: I really have to say they sound really good for the price. Trust me, you won't be disappointed. I have only used it for a day and it's easy to pair. I was thinking about getting airpods but didn't want to spend extract dollar and opted for this after a reviews. Only thing I have noticed is sometimes they feel like they are falling off the ear but it could by my ear size. Over all great product and love the fast delivery service.

author: Clara
title: Great sounding headphones!!!
content:
Why spend almost $300 on apple airpods when you got headphones like these?
Great quality sound and super fast charging case. Actually cancels out outside sound and has buttons for you to control, which in my opinion is better than the annoying touch controls on the airpords. The touch buttons give you better control and don't stop the music randomly like the airpods.

author: DB
title: TWS at a good price
content:
Build/Design: 4/5
These fashion a similar look to the AirPods with the addition of a physical button. Some people love, and some people hate it, I actually like it because you won’t accidentally hit a physical button as much as you would a touch sensitive one. They’re sturdy, higher quality plastic, and a strong magnet connection to the charging case.

The charging case provides hours of continuous playback, and the only drawback I had with these earbuds is occasionally trying to get them out. The magnet is strong.

Performance: 4/5
No issues connecting to my phone and MacBook. Very easy to do, and have 0 connection issues. I’ve been able to walk around through the majority of my house without losing connection (roughly 15-25ft range).

Overall Sound: 4/5
Sound is pretty good for this price level. Most TWS at this price point can have a cheap, can like sound but these have a full bass, wide mids, and clear highs.

Mic overall is pretty good, I work in an loud environment and these held up fine. They’re not most incredible for the mic as they don’t cancel out the noise, but they are usable and work in most environments.

Overall Review: 4/5
These are really good for the price, quality, and sound. They’re definitely not cheap, and they are well suited where they are.

author: Goony
title: Snug Fit Classic Sport Design and Ergnomic Feel
content: I really love the sound coming from this ear piece for Music That Plays Phenomenal sound like movie theater. It works great like a normal ear bud very easy to set up I recommend buying the one thing is that since it’s only so many dollar. it only comes with two bud and one case. This is better then Gel itch inside your ear. If one of my ear was not paining than I would of felt a lot better.

author: S83t
title: Good sound quality butts not a good fit for me
content: The sound quality of these headphones were excellent. the reason I returned them was because they would not stay in my ears. Every time I would smile they would pop out. They need to put rubber coating on them, in my opinion. I returned them.

author: David A. Ghali
title: Amazing Earbuds for an amazing price!
content: I got to say, I was very impressed with this product. I bought similar apple earbuds look alike in the past and they were very disappointing. They were either too big or don’t pair correctly or they break fast. This pair on the other hand was exceptional. The quality of sound is Stereo 5.0 superior quality. Making phone calls quality is great.  They fit perfectly. The charging case and battery life are awesome. This pair of earbuds has the same feel and look as the original apple ones at third of the price. Seller shipped very fast and I got them in no time. I definitely recommend this product from this seller.

author: Michael Kaufman
title: Excellent low cost wireless headphones.
content:
Excellent quality sound, comfortable, and they sit safely in my ears. Very good range.

The only thing is I wish there was a way to control the volume from the headphones.

Other than that,they are just great.

author: My Nguyen
title: Looks alike as Airpod and cost 1/3
content: Beautiful white earpod and looks fancy as Airpod but wont break your bank. The connection is easy. take it out of the case and it will connect to your device. Sound works great too. Love this

author: R3
title: Cost-effective quality little alternative to Airpods
content:
Pros:
- Music qualify is fine, not very clear or doesn't have bass
- Mic is good, works 4/5 times and the other party can hear just fine
- Charge time of case and earbuds both are pretty quick
- Pairing and unpairing is quick and easy, both for dual and mono
- Earbud controls works per the instructions
- Quite identical to Airpods, by the looks

Cons:
- The bluetooth earbuds are missing volume control
- Sometimes, the call quality suddenly goes bad
- Noice cancellation and music quality is not top notch

I wish there was a hook on the case for easier carrying around, but at this price, I couldn't ask more.

author: Andy0o0o
title: Pretty nice earbuds, works well.
content: These earbuds are pretty nice, better than I expected. The sound quality is good and I am also surprised at how well it connect as soon as I take it out of the case. I have a Android so did not want to get an airpods but I like the feel of the airpods so this is a great alternative. I hate those headphones with the rubbery earbuds.

author: Jong Oh Kim
title: Pleasant surprise!
content:
Honestly, these sound pretty good.
I was impressed when I first put them on.
They have a good bass punch, but not overpowering to the point where the audio is muddied.
These sound as good as in-ear headphones from other brands, without the need for the 'seal'.
These paired effortlessly to my phone, which is a great plus.

author: Sherry
title: Very surprising!
content: I did not think these headphone would be this great. I wanted to purchase some AirPods but I was afraid that they would get lost. I ordered these to try out something similar and to see how I would keep up with them. The sound quality is great, the fit in my ear very nicely. I have been doing all kinds of extra things to see if they would fall out and they have not yet. Forget the AirPods I will keep these.

author: hanke
title: Hands-free
content: $50 vs $200 for same quality and same battery life just a little bit sound quality different. I chose $50 one and I think I made the right move. I'm a construction worker and I need my hands-free during my work time and I don't like wires around my neck, so this product worth for the money.

author: Sharyn C.
title: Quality made and great alternative to expensive AirPods.
content: I’ve been purchasing items for the upcoming holidays, but decided to look for an affordable alternative to the standard (expensive) AirPods on the market and keep for myself. I received these on Friday and used them all weekend when buying groceries, working around the house, and even while at the gym to test out how well they stayed in my ears. I couldn’t be happier with the battery life and stability when wearing. Very happy with purchase and price point.

author: Harsh Shastri
title: Great Bluetooth earphones at reasonable price!
content: This is perfect bluetooth earphone for me. Sound quality is awesome. Fits nicely into the ears and doesn’t fall out while working out. Awesome performance. Highly recommendable product.

author: Jenny
title: Great so far! Fits well and responsive. Decent sounds.
content: Just got these and works better than other bluetooth ear buds! Love it. It immediately picked up and  to paired right away after charging.  This one is good compared to the other bluetooth ear pods I got. I had to return another brand and read the reviews for this one. I am please it fits better than billboard ear pods. I'm glad I got these!!I also wanted apple pods but too expensive,  these are great more affordable and I'm impressed with the responsiveness. I charged these and worked right away.  Unlike other ones I purchased. This had a discount too. I like how it fits better on my ear.  I'll update this review if anything changes but so far so good.

author: Dru Lattin
title: Better-than-airPods for Android
content:
Yes, they are cheap AirPod knockoffs. But that's a good thing, when they're designed this well! The audio isn't fantastic, but it's great for audiobooks and podcasts, or casual music listening. I especially appreciated the compact form factor and secure magnet in the lid.

One thing that makes these "better than" AirPods is that you can use them well with Android, cycling each side out of the charging case. They connect and disconnect securely, without any lag. Of course, the best feature is the price: you can use these without anxiety, since they are a fraction of the cost of the Apple version.

author: Ryan Geiger
title: One Size Fits Most
content: I like that these AirPods seem to have a tighter fit and are less likely to fall out u like other products of a similar design. The connection can get interrupted if you are moving around but that does not happen often. I like that they connect automatically once you take them out of the container as well. They have a good life of about 4 hours and do a good job of canceling other noise. If

author: Rachel Higgins
title: Didn’t fit in my ears.
content: I returned them, they were uncomfortable in my ears. I bought them to specifically run with and I didn’t feel they were securely sitting in my ear. I wouldn’t say I have little ears by any means, but they just didn’t rest or fit far enough in my ear that I would have liked.

author: Ruth
title: Pleasantly surprised!
content: I've been wanting to try ear buds that are truly wireless, so ordered these because they were affordable.  I'm impressed (at least so far) with the quality.  They arrived fully charged and paired easily with my phone.  They're comfortable in my ears, and the sound quality has been great, both listening to music/podcasts and during phone calls.  Definitely a good investment if you want to try wireless ear buds.

author: A. Lans
title: Better than my Airpod battery last almost 5 hours
content: Compare to airpod both or any side can run independently and last almost 5 hours of non stop playing without standby time, my Airpod only last almost just 2 hours on continuous non stop playing and we all use airpod at my work and when I used this they are always like is that the new airpod 2 lol

author: A Mom who reads
title: Sound, size, comfort are all top on these earbuds. Can use 1 or both.
content:
Sound, size, comfort are all top on these earbuds. Sound is clear, rich and has good low and high sound with over all great tone. I wish I could add a sound clip for you to listen to.
Can control on off on each . I can wear just one or both since they power on individually!  Very comfortable while listening working out at the gym, doing dishes in my kitchen or listening during the night when I can't sleep, My husband is super sensitive to noise while sleeping and other ear buds have made enough noise is bothered when I listen but not these! I listened for hours with him right next to me and he slept right through it. My teens usually make off with ear buds I order but I'm hiding these and keeping them for myself.  The case is a nice small size. I've tucked them in my pocket, dropped them in my purse and in my gym bag. They also charge very quickly. If you just haven't found the right ear buds order these, I really think you will be impressed.  My hands are very small so these look bigger than they are. I do recommend these.

author: appstatesoldier
title: Just as good as Apple
content: I have a pair of apple pods and I can honestly say these are very similar to the more expensive brand. The sound quality is great, no static or loss of connection. I am definitely buying another pair for my husband and daughter for Christmas!!

author: BJS
title: Great Product
content: Great inexpensive pair of blutooth ear buds. Worked right of the box with little or no fuss to setup and pair. Most impressive us battery life which is outstanding. These are a keeper!

author: Reina Del Rio
title: Nice Earbuds- Quality is a different story
content: I was surprised at the poor quality of these earbuds. Amazon usually carries good products. In this case, you get what you paid for! I returned mine and bought a pair of Bose wireless earbuds.

author: S. Hussain
title: Really like these
content: The battery seems to last forever, they automatically connect as soon as they are taken out of the case, and automatically turn off when put back in the case, and they are more comfortable then other similar ones that i have tried with prolonged wearing time.

author: Elliott
title: Comfort, Sound Quality, and Ease of Use.
content: I have had these for a few days now and I am pleasantly surprised on the quality of them. I used them all day at work today and had no issues getting them connected, and keeping them in place in my ears.
