They are actually quite comfortable which I didn't think would be true considering the shape, but they were. The sound quality was actually really decent as well, which was nice. Overall I think you get a lot for the price and they're not something to be overlooked.

author: Mike Malloy
title: Good value for the money
content: Good quality.  Easy to pair to phone and to use.  The quality of the sound was good and better than expected.  I have not been able to test out other functions yet.  I will update shortly.  Very satisfied with the purchase.

author: yeper
title: A great value for a very good quality ear bud!
content: I bought these as an alternative to the included iPhone ear buds without having to pay for a pods. I wear them while working in my office and to take calls and have not been disappointed! Sound quality is good for music and phone calls. They are very comfortable even after several hours.

author: caotrungtin
title: replicate airpod at 45$
content:
like :quite same as airpod, a little bigger than airpod, the sound quality is not bad compare to airpod, have button to change song and there are a few function with the button as well.
dont like : quite not fit small and medium ears, it is good for big ears. case cannot stand and still micro USB

author: Jorge Carlo Damiani
title: Simple.  Nice looking.  Does the job
content: They were a bday present for my daughter. She loves them.  White and shiny, similar to the AirPods. Easy to hook up and no dropped connection so far.  She is happy.

author: TheWife
title: Great quality earbuds
content: I super love the sound quality of this!!! I though wish it fits my ears though :( but seriously the sound quality of this earbuds is so good. My friend and husband wants to trade mine to theirs lol. I like that it is white it looks like a knock-off of airpods so it can deceive people at first look. For the price, this is worth the money.

author: Yi C Liou
title: Surprisingly clear
content: Blown away at the sound of these. Seriously shocked. Had low expectations for the price point. Hoping the stand the test of time with sweat from the work out. They came charged so I could right our of the box

author: Quinn
title: Too fragile and break easily
content:
Edit:
I’m very disappointed to make this edit. Turns out the right earbud didn’t want to stay in my ear, fell out as I was walking to work, and SHATTERED. The wires came undone and now it doesn’t work. :(
——————-
Original review:
These work AMAZING! I wanted wireless earbuds that are affordable, and these are exactly that! I tried other earbuds by other companies that arrived broken, had poor sound quality, didn't charge, etc. So far, I've had no problem with these. I'm so happy!

author: K Smith
title: Did not sync
content: Unfortunately, I could not get these to pair with the iPhone 11. Tried for a few days with no success.

author: Alicia Quigley
title: If you're looking for airpods, but don't want to pay the price, here's your best option!
content:
I like to write reviews for products I love and I try to give my most honest opinions because I read reviews and that's how I buy products. So here we go...

I'm a runner, so I'm always looking for new headphones that are comfortable and durable that get me through my miles for the day. I don't like the wires on my Apple headphones because I've been known to pull the wire directly out of my ears or phone and have to stop my run to fix it. I've always wanted Apple AirPods but didn't want to pay the price for these dainty, little headphones, so I took my search to Amazon to see what they offered. I did extensive research, read reviews, and by luck I stumbled upon these wireless pods. I bought these in anticipation for my next 5k, which was 2 days away from when I ordered these (thank you next day delivery!) and I was excited to use them.

Upon receiving, I noticed just how nicely packed they were and how cute the little charging case is, which is small and can fit in my pocket without looking bulky. They're easy to set up after reading the user manual, which I recommend, so I could figure out how to change songs, pause, or go back to a previous song. I haven't received any calls while using these, so I can't say how well the Bluetooth works for that, but I have high expectations. The sound quality is amazing and blocks out outside noises, which is great but also dangerous if you're outside and can't hear cars coming by, so definitely make sure you're paying attention to your surroundings. Overall, I'm really impressed with these earbuds and highly recommend these if you're looking for cheaper headphones without paying Apple's prices!!

author: DDDave
title: Buy them!  Great deal and amazing quality at any price.
content: Great Bluetooth earbuds all around. Sound quality is often sacrificed in cheaper products but not this one. The sound quality is equal to the wired headphones. They sync and pair effortlessly and have a nice 30’ range.  They auto sync to the last device paired so just take the buds out of the charging case and they are paired by the time they are in your ears.  The battery life is about 3 hrs as advertised. They charge in about 1 hour. The case charges the buds about 4- 5 times between case charge.  Heck of a deal here. I’ve had them for about a month and a half and still work perfectly.

author: Charles
title: One of the better fakePods out there
content:
I bought this to be my AirPods backup because I work in construction and I get dirty.  I'm quite impressed with these in terms of apple-like functionality and sound.  No other fakePods I own (probably 8) pair as fast these.  It's on par with the real AirPods.  The sound is also not bad either.  I would compare it simliar to AirPods 1 sound, which is a good thing because I can't stand the heavy bass on my AirPods 2.

Also to note, these are a smidge larger than real AirPods.  Just by a hair.  I found it actually blocks out ambient noise so that's a good thing!

author: prazebe
title: Good quality and design
content: Sounds good, a tiny bit bass heavy which is how I like my music. Has physical push buttons which is sometimes preferable over the touch activated buttons that are on BT headphones these days.

author: Justin and Kaylyn Salt
title: Incredibly Comfortable Earbuds!
content: Love these earbuds! The sound quality is good and the design is amazing! These headphones are designed similarly to AirPods, but at a fraction of the price. It has a physical button, which makes controlling the earbuds more confident. I love how you can use one or both earbuds without sacrificing quality. These earbuds are incredibly comfortable. Have worn them for over an hour without any ear fatigue. Would definitely recommend!!!

author: amalthe
title: Good sound, great range
content: These are really great! Ive purchased different kinds and this one had the best range for me. Sound quality is awesome. Really good wireless earbuds at a decent price.

author: Lori Medley
title: These are a Very Good Buy!
content:
Easy pairing & feels great in my ears. I have small ear canals & most buds make them sore, but these are quite different.
My only wish is that the volume was higher. Your phone controls the volume & mine is nearly maxed out. I've noticed that with any of the recent wireless buds I've bought. That said the volume is good.
Noise cancellation isn't maxes, but the music is able to br heard without pushing them deep in my ears. These are way better than any other wireless product I've bought. I think I've finally landed on a keeper!
